4294 //---------------------------------------------------------
4295 // changeState
4296 //---------------------------------------------------------
4297 
4298 void MuseScore::changeState(ScoreState val)
4299  {
4300  if (MScore::debugMode)
4301  qDebug("MuseScore::changeState: %s", stateName(val));
4302 
4303  // disallow change to edit modes if currently in play mode
4304  if (_sstate == STATE_PLAY && (val == STATE_EDIT || val & STATE_ALLTEXTUAL_EDIT || val & STATE_NOTE_ENTRY))
4305  return;
4306 
4307  static const char* stdNames[] = {
4308  "note-longa", "note-breve", "pad-note-1", "pad-note-2", "pad-note-4",
4309  "pad-note-8", "pad-note-16", "pad-note-32", "pad-note-64", "pad-note-128",
4310  "pad-note-256","pad-note-512","pad-note-1024","pad-rest", "rest"};
4311  static const char* tabNames[] = {
4312  "note-longa-TAB", "note-breve-TAB", "pad-note-1-TAB", "pad-note-2-TAB", "pad-note-4-TAB",
4313  "pad-note-8-TAB", "pad-note-16-TAB", "pad-note-32-TAB", "pad-note-64-TAB", "pad-note-128-TAB",
4314  "pad-note-256-TAB", "pad-note-512-TAB", "pad-note-1024-TAB", "pad-rest-TAB", "rest-TAB"};
4315  bool intoTAB = (_sstate != STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_TAB) && (val == STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_TAB);
4316  bool fromTAB = (_sstate == STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_TAB) && (val != STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_TAB);
4317  // if activating TAB note entry, swap "pad-note-...-TAB" shorctuts into "pad-note-..." actions
4318  if (intoTAB) {
4319  for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(stdNames)/sizeof(char*); ++i) {
4320  QAction* act = getAction(stdNames[i]);
4321  const Shortcut* srt = Shortcut::getShortcut(tabNames[i]);
4322  act->setShortcuts(srt->keys());
4323  }
4324  }
4325  // if de-ativating TAB note entry, restore shortcuts for "pad-note-..." actions
4326  else if (fromTAB) {
4327  for (unsigned i = 0; i < sizeof(stdNames)/sizeof(char*); ++i) {
4328  QAction* act = getAction(stdNames[i]);
4329  const Shortcut* srt = Shortcut::getShortcut(stdNames[i]);
4330  act->setShortcuts(srt->keys());
4331  }
4332  }
4333 
4334  bool enable = (val != STATE_DISABLED) && (val != STATE_LOCK);
4335 
4336  for (const Shortcut* s : Shortcut::shortcuts()) {
4337  QAction* a = s->action();
4338  if (!a)
4339  continue;
4340  if (enable && (s->key() == "undo"))
4341  a->setEnabled((s->state() & val) && (cs ? cs->undoStack()->canUndo() : false));
4342  else if (enable && (s->key() == "redo"))
4343  a->setEnabled((s->state() & val) && (cs ? cs->undoStack()->canRedo() : false));
4344  else if (enable && (s->key() == "cut"))
4345  a->setEnabled(cs && cs->selection().state() != SelState::NONE);
4346  else if (enable && (s->key() == "copy"))
4347  a->setEnabled(cs && (cs->selection().state() != SelState::NONE || val == STATE_FOTO));
4348  else if (enable && (s->key() == "select-similar-range"))
4349  a->setEnabled(cs && cs->selection().state() == SelState::RANGE);
4350  else if (enable && (s->key() == "synth-control" || s->key() == "toggle-mixer")) {
4351  Driver* driver = seq ? seq->driver() : 0;
4352  // a->setEnabled(driver && driver->getSynth());
4353  if (MScore::debugMode)
4354  qDebug("disable synth control");
4355  a->setEnabled(driver);
4356  }
4357  else {
4358  a->setEnabled(s->state() & val);
4359  }
4360  }
4361 
4362  if (getAction("join-measures")->isEnabled())
4363  getAction("join-measures")->setEnabled(cs && cs->masterScore()->excerpts().size() == 0);
4364  if (getAction("split-measure")->isEnabled())
4365  getAction("split-measure")->setEnabled(cs && cs->masterScore()->excerpts().size() == 0);
4366 
4367  // disabling top level menu entries does not
4368  // work for MAC
4369 
4370  QList<QObject*> ol = menuBar()->children();
4371  foreach(QObject* o, ol) {
4372  QMenu* menu = qobject_cast<QMenu*>(o);
4373  if (!menu)
4374  continue;
4375  QString s(menu->objectName());
4376  if (s == "File" || s == "Help" || s == "Edit" || s == "Plugins" || s == "View")
4377  continue;
4378  menu->setEnabled(enable);
4379  }
4380 
4381  menuWorkspaces->setEnabled(enable);
4382 
4383  transportTools->setEnabled(enable && !noSeq && seq && seq->isRunning());
4384  cpitchTools->setEnabled(enable);
4385  zoomBox->setEnabled(enable);
4386  entryTools->setEnabled(enable);
4387 
4388  if (_sstate == STATE_FOTO)
4389  updateInspector();
4390 
4391  //always hide drumtools to support hiding on switching docs, switching node entry mode off, etc.
4392  //it will be shown later if (_sstate == STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_DRUM)
4393  showDrumTools(0, 0);
4394 
4395  switch (val) {
4396  case STATE_DISABLED:
4397  showModeText(tr("No score"));
4398  if (debugger)
4399  debugger->hide();
4400  showPianoKeyboard(false);
4401  break;
4402  case STATE_NORMAL:
4403  showModeText(tr("Normal mode"));;
4404  break;
4405  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY:
4406  if (cv && !cv->noteEntryMode())
4407  cv->cmd("note-input");
4408  // fall through
4409  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_PITCHED:
4410  if (getAction("note-input-repitch")->isChecked()) {
4411  showModeText(tr("Repitch input mode"));
4412  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REPITCH);
4413  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REPITCH;
4414  }
4415  else if (getAction("note-input-rhythm")->isChecked()) {
4416  showModeText(tr("Rhythm input mode"));
4417  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::RHYTHM);
4418  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_RHYTHM;
4419  }
4420  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-auto")->isChecked()) {
4421  showModeText(tr("Realtime (automatic) note input mode"));
4422  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_AUTO);
4423  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_AUTO;
4424  }
4425  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-manual")->isChecked()) {
4426  showModeText(tr("Realtime (manual) note input mode"));
4427  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_MANUAL);
4428  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_MANUAL;
4429  }
4430  else if (getAction("note-input-timewise")->isChecked()) {
4431  showModeText(tr("Insert mode"));
4432  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::TIMEWISE);
4433  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_TIMEWISE;
4434  }
4435  else {
4436  showModeText(tr("Steptime note input mode"));
4437  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::STEPTIME);
4438  val = STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_STEPTIME;
4439  }
4440  break;
4441  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_DRUM:
4442  {
4443  if (getAction("note-input-repitch")->isChecked())
4444  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REPITCH);
4445  else if (getAction("note-input-rhythm")->isChecked())
4446  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::RHYTHM);
4447  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-auto")->isChecked())
4448  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_AUTO);
4449  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-manual")->isChecked())
4450  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_MANUAL);
4451  else if (getAction("note-input-timewise")->isChecked())
4452  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::TIMEWISE);
4453  else
4454  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::STEPTIME);
4455  showModeText(tr("Drumset input mode"));
4456  InputState& is = cs->inputState();
4457  showDrumTools(is.drumset(), cs->staff(is.track() / VOICES));
4458  if (_drumTools)
4459  is.setDrumNote(_drumTools->selectedDrumNote());
4460  }
4461  break;
4462  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_TAB:
4463  if (getAction("note-input-repitch")->isChecked())
4464  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REPITCH);
4465  else if (getAction("note-input-rhythm")->isChecked())
4466  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::RHYTHM);
4467  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-auto")->isChecked())
4468  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_AUTO);
4469  else if (getAction("note-input-realtime-manual")->isChecked())
4470  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_MANUAL);
4471  else if (getAction("note-input-timewise")->isChecked())
4472  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::TIMEWISE);
4473  else
4474  cs->setNoteEntryMethod(NoteEntryMethod::STEPTIME);
4475  showModeText(tr("TAB input mode"));
4476  break;
4477  case STATE_EDIT:
4478  showModeText(tr("Edit mode"));
4479  break;
4480  case STATE_TEXT_EDIT:
4481  showModeText(tr("Text edit mode"));
4482  break;
4483  case STATE_LYRICS_EDIT:
4484  showModeText(tr("Lyrics edit mode"));
4485  break;
4486  case STATE_HARMONY_FIGBASS_EDIT:
4487  showModeText(tr("Chord symbol/figured bass edit mode"));
4488  break;
4489  case STATE_PLAY:
4490  showModeText(tr("Play"), false); // don't talk over playback
4491  break;
4492  case STATE_FOTO:
4493  showModeText(tr("Image capture mode"));
4494  updateInspector();
4495  break;
4496  case STATE_LOCK:
4497  showModeText(tr("Score locked"));
4498  break;
4499  default:
4500  qFatal("MuseScore::changeState: illegal state %d", val);
4501  break;
4502  }
4503  if (paletteWidget)
4504  paletteWidget->setDisabled(val == STATE_PLAY || val == STATE_DISABLED);
4505  if (selectionWindow)
4506  selectionWindow->setDisabled(val == STATE_PLAY || val == STATE_DISABLED);
4507  QAction* a = getAction("note-input");
4508  bool noteEntry = val & STATE_NOTE_ENTRY;
4509  a->setChecked(noteEntry);
4510  _sstate = val;
4511 
4512  emit scoreStateChanged(_sstate);
4513 
4514  Element* e = cv && (_sstate & STATE_ALLTEXTUAL_EDIT || _sstate == STATE_EDIT) ? cv->getEditElement() : 0;
4515  if (!e) {
4516  textTools()->hide();
4517  if (textTools()->kbAction()->isChecked())
4518  textTools()->kbAction()->setChecked(false);
4519  }
4520  else {
4521  if (e->isTextBase()) {
4522  textTools()->updateTools(cv->getEditData());
4523  if (!(e->isFiguredBass() || e->isHarmony())) { // do not show text tools for f.b.
4524  if (timelineScrollArea() && timelineScrollArea()->isVisible()) {
4525  if (dockWidgetArea(timelineScrollArea()) != dockWidgetArea(textTools()) || timelineScrollArea()->isFloating()) {
4526  QSizePolicy policy(QSizePolicy::Maximum, QSizePolicy::Maximum);
4527  textTools()->widget()->setSizePolicy(policy);
4528  }
4529  else {
4530  QSizePolicy policy(QSizePolicy::Expanding, QSizePolicy::Expanding);
4531  textTools()->widget()->setSizePolicy(policy);
4532  }
4533  }
4534  else {
4535  QSizePolicy policy(QSizePolicy::Maximum, QSizePolicy::Maximum);
4536  textTools()->widget()->setSizePolicy(policy);
4537  }
4538  if (timelineScrollArea())
4539  splitDockWidget(textTools(), timelineScrollArea(), Qt::Vertical);
4540  textTools()->show();
4541  }
4542  }
4543  if (_inspector)
4544  _inspector->update(e->score());
4545  }
4546  }

4659 //---------------------------------------------------------
4660 // readSettings
4661 //---------------------------------------------------------
4662 
4663 void MuseScore::readSettings()
4664  {
4665  int margin = 100;
4666  int offset = margin / 2;
4667  int w = 1024;
4668  int h = 768;
4669  QScreen* screen = QGuiApplication::primaryScreen();
4670  const QSize screenSize = screen->availableSize();
4671  if (screenSize.width() - margin > w)
4672  w = screenSize.width() - margin;
4673  else
4674  offset = 0;
4675  if (screenSize.height() - margin > h)
4676  h = screenSize.height() - margin;
4677 
4678  resize(QSize(w, h)); //ensure default size if no geometry in settings
4679  move(offset, 0);
4680  if (useFactorySettings) {
4681  QList<int> sizes;
4682  sizes << 500 << 100;
4683  mainWindow->setSizes(sizes);
4684  mscore->showPalette(true);
4685  mscore->showInspector(true);
4686  return;
4687  }
4688 
4689  MuseScore::restoreGeometry(this);
4690 
4691  // Grab the mixer visible state before the beginGroup.
4692  // Previously the showMixer() call was made at the end of
4693  // main(). Now it's made inside this beginGroup / endGroup.
4694  // This code ensures user previous setting is respected when
4695  // updating their version of MuseScore.
4696  bool mixerVisible = settings.value("mixerVisible", "0").toBool();
4697  settings.beginGroup("MainWindow");
4698  mainWindow->restoreState(settings.value("debuggerSplitter").toByteArray());
4699  mainWindow->setOpaqueResize(false);
4700  scorePageLayoutChanged();
4701 
4702  //for some reason when MuseScore starts maximized the screen-reader
4703  //doesn't respond to QAccessibleEvents --> so force normal mode
4704  if (isMaximized() && QAccessible::isActive()) {
4705  showNormal();
4706  }
4707  mscore->showPalette(settings.value("showPanel", "1").toBool());
4708  mscore->showInspector(settings.value("showInspector", "1").toBool());
4709  mscore->showPianoKeyboard(settings.value("showPianoKeyboard", "0").toBool());
4710  mscore->showSelectionWindow(settings.value("showSelectionWindow", "0").toBool());
4711  mscore->showMixer(mixerVisible);
4712 
4713  restoreState(settings.value("state").toByteArray());
4714  //if we were in full screen mode, go to maximized mode
4715  if (isFullScreen()) {
4716  showMaximized();
4717  }
4718 
4719  _horizontalSplit = settings.value("split", true).toBool();
4720  bool splitScreen = settings.value("splitScreen", false).toBool();
4721  if (splitScreen) {
4722  splitWindow(_horizontalSplit);
4723  QAction* a = getAction(_horizontalSplit ? "split-h" : "split-v");
4724  a->setChecked(true);
4725  }
4726  splitter->restoreState(settings.value("splitter").toByteArray());
4727  settings.endGroup();
4728 
4729  QAction* a = getAction("toggle-fileoperations");
4730  a->setChecked(!fileTools->isHidden());
4731 
4732  a = getAction("toggle-transport");
4733  a->setChecked(!transportTools->isHidden());
4734 
4735  a = getAction("toggle-concertpitch");
4736  a->setChecked(!cpitchTools->isHidden());
4737 
4738  a = getAction("toggle-imagecapture");
4739  a->setChecked(!fotoTools->isHidden());
4740 
4741  a = getAction("toggle-noteinput");
4742  a->setChecked(!entryTools->isHidden());
4743  }

4745 //---------------------------------------------------------
4746 // play
4747 // play note for preferences.defaultPlayDuration
4748 //---------------------------------------------------------
4749 
4750 void MuseScore::play(Element* e) const
4751  {
4752  if (noSeq || !(seq && seq->isRunning()) || !preferences.getBool(PREF_SCORE_NOTE_PLAYONCLICK))
4753  return;
4754 
4755  if (e->isNote()) {
4756  Note* note = toNote(e);
4757  play(e, note->ppitch());
4758  }
4759  else if (e->isChord()) {
4760  seq->stopNotes();
4761  Chord* c = toChord(e);
4762  Part* part = c->staff()->part();
4763  Fraction tick = c->segment() ? c->segment()->tick() : Fraction(0,1);
4764  Instrument* instr = part->instrument(tick);
4765  for (Note* n : c->notes()) {
4766  const int channel = instr->channel(n->subchannel())->channel();
4767  seq->startNote(channel, n->ppitch(), 80, n->tuning());
4768  }
4769  seq->startNoteTimer(MScore::defaultPlayDuration);
4770  }
4771  else if (e->isHarmony()
4772  && preferences.getBool(PREF_SCORE_HARMONY_PLAY_ONEDIT)) {
4773  seq->stopNotes();
4774  Harmony* h = toHarmony(e);
4775  if (!h->isRealizable())
4776  return;
4777  RealizedHarmony r = h->getRealizedHarmony();
4778  QList<int> pitches = r.pitches();
4779 
4780  const Channel* hChannel = e->part()->harmonyChannel();
4781  if (!hChannel)
4782  return;
4783 
4784  int channel = hChannel->channel();
4785 
4786  // reset the cc that is used for single note dynamics, if any
4787  int cc = synthesizerState().ccToUse();
4788  if (cc != -1)
4789  seq->sendEvent(NPlayEvent(ME_CONTROLLER, channel, cc, 80));
4790 
4791  for (int pitch : pitches)
4792  seq->startNote(channel, pitch, 80, 0);
4793  seq->startNoteTimer(MScore::defaultPlayDuration);
4794  }
4795  }
4796 
4797 void MuseScore::play(Element* e, int pitch) const
4798  {
4799  if (noSeq || !(seq && seq->isRunning()))
4800  return;
4801  if (preferences.getBool(PREF_SCORE_NOTE_PLAYONCLICK) && e->isNote()) {
4802  Note* note = static_cast<Note*>(e);
4803 
4804  Note* masterNote = note;
4805  if (note->linkList().size() > 1) {
4806  for (ScoreElement* se_ : note->linkList()) {
4807  if (se_->score() == note->masterScore() && se_->isNote()) {
4808  masterNote = toNote(se_);
4809  break;
4810  }
4811  }
4812  }
4813 
4814  Fraction tick = masterNote->chord()->tick();
4815  if (tick < Fraction(0,1))
4816  tick = Fraction(0,1);
4817  Instrument* instr = masterNote->part()->instrument(tick);
4818  const int channel = instr->channel(masterNote->subchannel())->channel();
4819 
4820  // reset the cc that is used for single note dynamics, if any
4821  int cc = synthesizerState().ccToUse();
4822  if (cc != -1)
4823  seq->sendEvent(NPlayEvent(ME_CONTROLLER, channel, cc, 80));
4824 
4825  seq->startNote(channel, pitch, 80, MScore::defaultPlayDuration, masterNote->tuning());
4826  }
4827  }

4920 //---------------------------------------------------------
4921 // setZoom
4922 // Sets the zoom type and the logical free-zoom level.
4923 // logicalFreeZoomLevel is optional and may be omitted unless index is ZoomIndex::ZOOM_FREE.
4924 //---------------------------------------------------------
4925 
4926 void MuseScore::setZoom(const ZoomIndex index, const qreal logicalFreeZoomLevel/* = 0.0*/)
4927  {
4928  zoomAndSavePrevious([=]() { cv->setLogicalZoom(index, cv->calculateLogicalZoomLevel(index, logicalFreeZoomLevel)); });
4929  }
4930 
4931 //---------------------------------------------------------
4932 // setZoomWithToggle
4933 // Sets the specified zoom type, or toggles back to the previous zoom state if the zoom type is already the specified one.
4934 //---------------------------------------------------------
4935 
4936 void MuseScore::setZoomWithToggle(const ZoomIndex index)
4937  {
4938  if (cv) {
4939  const ZoomIndex currentZoomIndex = cv->zoomIndex();
4940  if (currentZoomIndex != index) {
4941  // The current zoom type isn't the specified one, so just set it to that.
4942  setZoom(index);
4943  }
4944  else {
4945  // The current zoom type is already the specified one, so toggle back to the previous zoom state.
4946  setZoom(cv->previousZoomIndex(), cv->previousLogicalZoomLevel());
4947  }
4948  }
4949  }

4961 //---------------------------------------------------------
4962 // zoomAndSavePrevious
4963 // Calls the specified zoom function and also saves the previous zoom state if it has changed by the zoom function.
4964 //---------------------------------------------------------
4965 
4966 void MuseScore::zoomAndSavePrevious(const std::function<void(void)>& zoomFunction)
4967  {
4968  if (cv) {
4969  // Make a copy of the current zoom state before it changes.
4970  const auto previousLogicalZoom = cv->logicalZoom();
4971 
4972  // Zoom!
4973  zoomFunction();
4974 
4975  // Save the previous zoom state, but only if the zoom state has actually changed.
4976  if (cv->logicalZoom() != previousLogicalZoom)
4977  cv->setPreviousLogicalZoom(previousLogicalZoom);
4978  }
4979  }

4986 void MuseScore::updateZoomBox(const ZoomIndex index, const qreal logicalLevel)
4987  {
4988  const QSignalBlocker blocker(zoomBox);
4989  zoomBox->setLogicalZoom(index, logicalLevel);
4990  }

4995 //---------------------------------------------------------
4996 
4997 void MuseScore::setPos(const Fraction& t)
4998  {
4999  if (cs == 0 || t < Fraction(0,1))
5000  return;
5001 
5002  TimeSigMap* s = cs->sigmap();
5003  int bar, beat, tick;
5004  s->tickValues(t.ticks(), &bar, &beat, &tick);
5005  _positionLabel->setText(QString("%1:%2:%3")
5006  .arg(bar + 1, 3, 10, QLatin1Char(' '))
5007  .arg(beat + 1, 2, 10, QLatin1Char('0'))
5008  .arg(tick, 3, 10, QLatin1Char('0'))
5009  );
5010  }

5092 //---------------------------------------------------------
5093 // writeSessionFile
5094 //---------------------------------------------------------
5095 
5096 void MuseScore::writeSessionFile(bool cleanExit)
5097  {
5098 // qDebug("write session file");
5099 
5100  QDir dir;
5101  dir.mkpath(dataPath);
5102  QFile f(dataPath + "/session");
5103  if (!f.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly)) {
5104  qDebug("cannot create session file <%s>", qPrintable(f.fileName()));
5105  return;
5106  }
5107  XmlWriter xml(0, &f);
5108  xml.header();
5109  xml.stag(QStringLiteral("museScore version=\"" MSC_VERSION "\" full-version=\"%1\"").arg(fullVersion()));
5110  xml.tagE(cleanExit ? "clean" : "dirty");
5111 
5112  foreach(MasterScore* score, scoreList) {
5113  xml.stag("Score");
5114  xml.tag("created", score->created());
5115  xml.tag("dirty", score->dirty());
5116 
5117  QString path;
5118  if (score->importedFilePath().isEmpty()) {
5119  // score was not imported from another format, e.g. MIDI file
5120  path = score->masterScore()->fileInfo()->absoluteFilePath();
5121  }
5122  else if (score->masterScore()->fileInfo()->exists()) { // score was saved
5123  path = score->masterScore()->fileInfo()->absoluteFilePath();
5124  }
5125  else { // score was imported but not saved - store original file (e.g. MIDI) path
5126  path = score->importedFilePath();
5127  }
5128 
5129  if (cleanExit || score->tmpName().isEmpty()) {
5130  xml.tag("path", path);
5131  }
5132  else {
5133  xml.tag("name", path);
5134  xml.tag("path", score->tmpName());
5135  }
5136  xml.etag();
5137  }
5138  int tab = 0;
5139  int idx = 0;
5140  for (int i = 0; i < tab1->count(); ++i) {
5141  ScoreView* v = tab1->view(i);
5142  if (v) {
5143  if (v == cv) {
5144  tab = 0;
5145  idx = i;
5146  }
5147  xml.stag("ScoreView");
5148  xml.tag("tab", tab); // 0 instead of "tab" does not work
5149  xml.tag("idx", i);
5150  if (v->zoomIndex() == ZoomIndex::ZOOM_FREE)
5151  xml.tag("mag", v->logicalZoomLevel());
5152  else
5153  xml.tag("magIdx", int(v->zoomIndex()));
5154  xml.tag("x", v->xoffset() / DPMM);
5155  xml.tag("y", v->yoffset() / DPMM);
5156  xml.etag();
5157  }
5158  }
5159  if (splitScreen()) {
5160  for (int i = 0; i < tab2->count(); ++i) {
5161  ScoreView* v = tab2->view(i);
5162  if (v) {
5163  if (v == cv) {
5164  tab = 1;
5165  idx = i;
5166  }
5167  xml.stag("ScoreView");
5168  xml.tag("tab", 1);
5169  xml.tag("idx", i);
5170  if (v->zoomIndex() == ZoomIndex::ZOOM_FREE)
5171  xml.tag("mag", v->logicalZoomLevel());
5172  else
5173  xml.tag("magIdx", int(v->zoomIndex()));
5174  xml.tag("x", v->xoffset() / DPMM);
5175  xml.tag("y", v->yoffset() / DPMM);
5176  xml.etag();
5177  }
5178  }
5179  }
5180  xml.tag("tab", tab);
5181  xml.tag("idx", idx);
5182  xml.etag();
5183  f.close();
5184  if (cleanExit) {
5185  // TODO: remove all temporary session backup files
5186  }
5187  }

5204 //---------------------------------------------------------
5205 // autoSaveTimerTimeout
5206 //---------------------------------------------------------
5207 
5208 void MuseScore::autoSaveTimerTimeout()
5209  {
5210  bool sessionChanged = false;
5211 
5212  ScoreLoad sl; //disable debug message "no active command"
5213 
5214  for (MasterScore* s : scoreList) {
5215  if (s->autosaveDirty()) {
5216  qDebug("<%s>", qPrintable(s->fileInfo()->completeBaseName()));
5217  QString tmp = s->tmpName();
5218  if (!tmp.isEmpty()) {
5219  QFileInfo fi(tmp);
5220  // TODO: cannot catch exception here:
5221  s->saveCompressedFile(fi, false, false); // no thumbnail
5222  }
5223  else {
5224  QDir dir;
5225  dir.mkpath(dataPath);
5226  QTemporaryFile tf(dataPath + "/scXXXXXX.mscz");
5227  tf.setAutoRemove(false); // do not remove when tf goes out of scope!
5228  if (!tf.open()) {
5229  qDebug("autoSaveTimerTimeout(): create temporary file failed");
5230  return;
5231  }
5232  s->setTmpName(tf.fileName());
5233 
5234  QString fileName = QFileInfo(tf.fileName()).completeBaseName() + ".mscx";
5235  s->saveCompressedFile(&tf, fileName, false, false); // no thumbnail
5236 
5237  tf.close();
5238  sessionChanged = true;
5239  }
5240  s->setAutosaveDirty(false);
5241  }
5242  }
5243  if (sessionChanged)
5244  writeSessionFile(false);
5245  if (preferences.getBool(PREF_APP_AUTOSAVE_USEAUTOSAVE)) {
5246  int t = preferences.getInt(PREF_APP_AUTOSAVE_AUTOSAVETIME) * 60 * 1000;
5247  autoSaveTimer->start(t);
5248  }
5249  }
5250 
5251 class CallOnReturn {
5252  std::function<void()> f;
5253  public:
5254  CallOnReturn(std::function<void()> func) : f(std::move(func)) {}
5255  CallOnReturn(const CallOnReturn&) = delete;
5256  CallOnReturn& operator=(const CallOnReturn&) = delete;
5257  ~CallOnReturn() { f(); }
5258  };
5259 
5260 //---------------------------------------------------------
5261 // restoreSession
5262 // Restore last session. If "always" is true, then restore
5263 // last session even on a clean exit else only if last
5264 // session ended abnormal.
5265 // Return true if a session was found and restored.
5266 //---------------------------------------------------------
5267 
5268 bool MuseScore::restoreSession(bool always)
5269  {
5270  bool sessionFileFound = false;
5271  bool cleanExit = false;
5272  QString sessionFullVersion;
5273 
5274  CallOnReturn onReturn([this, &sessionFileFound, &sessionFullVersion, &cleanExit]() {
5275  sessionStatusObserver.prevSessionStatus(sessionFileFound, sessionFullVersion, cleanExit);
5276  });
5277 
5278  QFile f(dataPath + "/session");
5279  if (!f.exists())
5280  return false;
5281  if (!f.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
5282  qDebug("Cannot open session file <%s>", qPrintable(f.fileName()));
5283  return false;
5284  }
5285  sessionFileFound = true;
5286 
5287  XmlReader e(&f);
5288  int tab = 0;
5289  int idx = -1;
5290  while (e.readNextStartElement()) {
5291  if (e.name() == "museScore") {
5292  /* QString version = e.attribute(QString("version"));
5293  QStringList sl = version.split('.');
5294  int v = sl[0].toInt() * 100 + sl[1].toInt();
5295  */
5296  sessionFullVersion = e.attribute("full-version");
5297  while (e.readNextStartElement()) {
5298  const QStringRef& tag(e.name());
5299  if (tag == "clean") {
5300  cleanExit = true;
5301  if (!always)
5302  return false;
5303  e.readNext();
5304  }
5305  else if (tag == "dirty") {
5306  QMessageBox::StandardButton b = QMessageBox::question(0,
5307  tr("MuseScore"),
5308  tr("The previous session quit unexpectedly.\n\nRestore session?"),
5309  QMessageBox::Yes | QMessageBox::No,
5310  QMessageBox::Yes
5311  );
5312  if (b != QMessageBox::Yes)
5313  return false;
5314  e.readNext();
5315  }
5316  else if (tag == "Score") {
5317  QString name;
5318  bool created = false;
5319  while (e.readNextStartElement()) {
5320  const QStringRef& t(e.name());
5321  if (t == "name")
5322  name = e.readElementText();
5323  else if (t == "created")
5324  created = e.readInt();
5325  else if (t == "dirty")
5326  /*int dirty =*/ e.readInt();
5327  else if (t == "path") {
5328  Score* score = openScore(e.readElementText(), false, true, name);
5329  if (score) {
5330  if (cleanExit) {
5331  // override if last session did a clean exit
5332  created = false;
5333  }
5334  score->setCreated(created);
5335  }
5336  else {
5337  //! NOTE Return true so that there is no attempt to open this file again
5338  //! See: static void loadScores(const QStringList& argv)
5339  return true;
5340  }
5341  }
5342  else {
5343  e.unknown();
5344  return false;
5345  }
5346  }
5347  }
5348  else if (tag == "ScoreView") {
5349  qreal x = 0.0;
5350  qreal y = 0.0;
5351  qreal logicalZoomLevel = 1.0;
5352  ZoomIndex zoomIndex = ZoomIndex::ZOOM_FREE;
5353  int tab3 = 0;
5354  int idx1 = 0;
5355  while (e.readNextStartElement()) {
5356  const QStringRef& t(e.name());
5357  if (t == "tab")
5358  tab3 = e.readInt();
5359  else if (t == "idx")
5360  idx1 = e.readInt();
5361  else if (t == "mag")
5362  logicalZoomLevel = e.readDouble();
5363  else if (t == "magIdx") {
5364  zoomIndex = ZoomIndex(e.readInt());
5365 
5366  // The zoom level isn't saved along with the index, so reconstruct it if possible.
5367  const auto i = std::find(zoomEntries.cbegin(), zoomEntries.cend(), zoomIndex);
5368  if ((i != zoomEntries.cend()) && i->isNumericPreset())
5369  logicalZoomLevel = i->level / 100.0;
5370  }
5371  else if (t == "x")
5372  x = e.readDouble() * DPMM;
5373  else if (t == "y")
5374  y = e.readDouble() * DPMM;
5375  else {
5376  e.unknown();
5377  return false;
5378  }
5379  }
5380  (tab3 == 0 ? tab1 : tab2)->queueInitScoreView(idx1, logicalZoomLevel, zoomIndex, x, y);
5381  }
5382  else if (tag == "tab")
5383  tab = e.readInt();
5384  else if (tag == "idx")
5385  idx = e.readInt();
5386  else {
5387  e.unknown();
5388  return false;
5389  }
5390  }
5391  }
5392  else {
5393  e.unknown();
5394  return false;
5395  }
5396  }
5397  setCurrentView(tab, idx);
5398  return true;
5399  }

5401 //---------------------------------------------------------
5402 // splitWindow
5403 //---------------------------------------------------------
5404 
5405 void MuseScore::splitWindow(bool horizontal)
5406  {
5407  if (!_splitScreen) {
5408  if (tab2 == 0) {
5409  tab2 = createScoreTab();
5410  splitter->addWidget(tab2);
5411  }
5412  tab2->setVisible(true);
5413  _splitScreen = true;
5414  _horizontalSplit = horizontal;
5415  splitter->setOrientation(_horizontalSplit ? Qt::Horizontal : Qt::Vertical);
5416  if (!scoreList.isEmpty()) {
5417  tab2->setCurrentIndex(0);
5418  MasterScore* s = scoreList[0];
5419  s->setLayoutAll();
5420  s->update();
5421  setCurrentView(1, 0);
5422  }
5423  emit windowSplit(true);
5424  }
5425  else {
5426  if (_horizontalSplit == horizontal) {
5427  _splitScreen = false;
5428  tab2->setVisible(false);
5429  setCurrentView(0, tab1->currentIndex());
5430  emit windowSplit(false);
5431  }
5432  else {
5433  _horizontalSplit = horizontal;
5434  splitter->setOrientation(_horizontalSplit ? Qt::Horizontal : Qt::Vertical);
5435  }
5436  }
5437  getAction("split-h")->setChecked(_splitScreen && _horizontalSplit);
5438  getAction("split-v")->setChecked(_splitScreen && !_horizontalSplit);
5439  }

5450  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_PITCHED: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_STAFF_PITCHED";

5454  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_STEPTIME: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_STEPTIME";
5455  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REPITCH: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REPITCH";
5456  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_RHYTHM: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_RHYTHM";
5457  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_AUTO: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_AUTO";
5458  case STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_MANUAL: return "STATE_NOTE_ENTRY_METHOD_REALTIME_MANUAL";
5459  case STATE_EDIT: return "STATE_EDIT";
5460  case STATE_TEXT_EDIT: return "STATE_TEXT_EDIT";
5461  case STATE_LYRICS_EDIT: return "STATE_LYRICS_EDIT";
5462  case STATE_HARMONY_FIGBASS_EDIT: return "STATE_HARMONY_FIGBASS_EDIT";
5463  case STATE_PLAY: return "STATE_PLAY";
5464  case STATE_FOTO: return "STATE_FOTO";
5465  default: return "??";

5631 //---------------------------------------------------------
5632 // networkFinished
5633 //---------------------------------------------------------
5634 
5635 void MuseScore::networkFinished()
5636  {
5637  QNetworkReply* reply = qobject_cast<QNetworkReply*>(QObject::sender());
5638  if (reply->error() != QNetworkReply::NoError) {
5639  qDebug("Error while checking update [%s]", qPrintable(reply->errorString()));
5640  return;
5641  }
5642  QByteArray ha = reply->rawHeader("Content-Disposition");
5643  QString s(ha);
5644  QString name;
5645  QRegExp re(".*filename=\"(.*)\"");
5646 
5647  if (!s.isEmpty() && re.indexIn(s) != -1) {
5648  name = re.cap(1);
5649  }
5650  else {
5651  QUrl url = reply->url();
5652  QString path = url.path();
5653  qDebug("Path <%s>", qPrintable(path));
5654  QFileInfo fi(path);
5655  name = fi.fileName();
5656  }
5657 
5658  qDebug("header <%s>", qPrintable(s));
5659  qDebug("name <%s>", qPrintable(name));
5660 
5661  QByteArray dta = reply->readAll();
5662  QString tmpName = QDir::tempPath () + "/"+ name;
5663  QFile f(tmpName);
5664  f.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly);
5665  f.write(dta);
5666  f.close();
5667 
5668  reply->deleteLater();
5669 
5670  Score* score = openScore(tmpName);
5671  // delete the temp file created above
5672  QFile::remove(tmpName);
5673  if (!score) {
5674  qDebug("readScore failed");
5675  return;
5676  }
5677  score->setCreated(true);
5678  }

5685 void MuseScore::loadFile(const QString& s)
5686  {

5688  }
5689 
5690 void MuseScore::loadFile(const QUrl& url)
5691  {
5692  QEventLoop loop;
5693  QNetworkReply* nr = mscore->networkManager()->get(QNetworkRequest(url));
5694  connect(nr, SIGNAL(finished()), this,
5695  SLOT(networkFinished()));
5696  connect(nr, SIGNAL(finished()), &loop, SLOT(quit()));
5697  loop.exec();
5698  }

5739 //---------------------------------------------------------
5740 // selectElementDialog
5741 //---------------------------------------------------------
5742 
5743 void MuseScore::selectElementDialog(Element* e)
5744  {
5745  Score* score = e->score();
5746  if (e->isNote()) {
5747  Note* n = toNote(e);
5748  SelectNoteDialog sd(n, 0);
5749  // hide same string option if it doesn't make sense for the instrument
5750  if (n->staff()->part()->instrument()->stringData()->strings() == 0)
5751  sd.setSameStringVisible(false);
5752  if (sd.exec()) {
5753  NotePattern pattern;
5754  sd.setPattern(&pattern);
5755 
5756  if (sd.isInSelection())
5757  score->scanElementsInRange(&pattern, Score::collectNoteMatch);
5758  else
5759  score->scanElements(&pattern, Score::collectNoteMatch);
5760 
5761  if (sd.doReplace()) {
5762  score->select(0, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
5763  for (Note* ee : pattern.el)
5764  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5765  }
5766  else if (sd.doSubtract()) {
5767  QList<Element*> sl(score->selection().elements());
5768  for (Note* ee : pattern.el)
5769  sl.removeOne(ee);
5770  score->select(0, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
5771  for (Element* ee : sl)
5772  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5773  }
5774  else if (sd.doAdd()) {
5775  QList<Element*> sl(score->selection().elements());
5776  for (Note* ee : pattern.el) {
5777  if(!sl.contains(ee))
5778  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5779  }
5780  }
5781  }
5782  }
5783  else {
5784  SelectDialog sd(e, 0);
5785  if (sd.exec()) {
5786  ElementPattern pattern;
5787  sd.setPattern(&pattern);
5788 
5789  if (sd.isInSelection())
5790  score->scanElementsInRange(&pattern, Score::collectMatch);
5791  else
5792  score->scanElements(&pattern, Score::collectMatch);
5793 
5794  if (sd.doReplace()) {
5795  score->select(0, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
5796  for (Element* ee : pattern.el)
5797  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5798  }
5799  else if (sd.doSubtract()) {
5800  QList<Element*> sl(score->selection().elements());
5801  for (Element* ee : pattern.el)
5802  sl.removeOne(ee);
5803  score->select(0, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
5804  for (Element* ee : sl)
5805  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5806  }
5807  else if (sd.doAdd()) {
5808  QList<Element*> sl(score->selection().elements());
5809  for (Element* ee : pattern.el) {
5810  if(!sl.contains(ee))
5811  score->select(ee, SelectType::ADD, 0);
5812  }
5813  }
5814  }
5815  }
5816  if (score->selectionChanged()) {
5817  score->setSelectionChanged(false);
5818  SelState ss = score->selection().state();
5819  selectionChanged(ss);
5820  }
5821  }

5846 //---------------------------------------------------------
5847 // drawHandle
5848 //---------------------------------------------------------
5849 
5850 QRectF drawHandle(QPainter& p, const QPointF& pos, bool active)
5851  {
5852  p.save();
5853  p.setPen(QPen(QColor(MScore::selectColor[0]), 2.0/p.worldTransform().toAffine().m11()));
5854  if (active)
5855  p.setBrush(MScore::selectColor[0]);
5856  else
5857  p.setBrush(Qt::NoBrush);
5858  qreal w = 8.0 / p.worldTransform().toAffine().m11();
5859  qreal h = 8.0 / p.worldTransform().toAffine().m22();
5860 
5861  QRectF r(-w/2, -h/2, w, h);
5862  r.translate(pos);
5863  p.drawRect(r);
5864  p.restore();
5865  return r;
5866  }
5867 
5868 //---------------------------------------------------------
5869 // transpose
5870 //---------------------------------------------------------
5871 
5872 void MuseScore::transpose()
5873  {
5874  if (cs->last() == 0) // empty score?
5875  return;
5876 
5877  bool noSelection = cs->selection().isNone();
5878  if (noSelection)
5879  cs->cmdSelectAll();
5880  bool rangeSelection = cs->selection().isRange();
5881  TransposeDialog td;
5882 
5883  // TRANSPOSE_TO_KEY and "transpose keys" is only possible if selection state is SelState::RANGE
5884  td.enableTransposeKeys(rangeSelection);
5885  td.enableTransposeToKey(rangeSelection);
5886  td.enableTransposeChordNames(rangeSelection);
5887 
5888  int startStaffIdx = 0;
5889  int endStaffIdx = 0;
5890  Fraction startTick = Fraction(0,1);
5891  if (rangeSelection) {
5892  startStaffIdx = cs->selection().staffStart();
5893  endStaffIdx = cs->selection().staffEnd();
5894  startTick = cs->selection().tickStart();
5895  }
5896 
5897  // find the key of the first pitched staff
5898  Key key = Key::C;
5899  for (int i = startStaffIdx; i < endStaffIdx; ++i) {
5900  Staff* staff = cs->staff(i);
5901  if (staff->isPitchedStaff(startTick)) {
5902  key = staff->key(startTick);
5903  if (!cs->styleB(Sid::concertPitch)) {
5904  int diff = staff->part()->instrument(startTick)->transpose().chromatic;
5905  if (diff)
5906  key = transposeKey(key, diff, staff->part()->preferSharpFlat());
5907  }
5908  break;
5909  }
5910  }
5911 
5912  td.setKey(key);
5913  if (!td.exec())
5914  return;
5915 
5916  cs->transpose(td.mode(), td.direction(), td.transposeKey(), td.transposeInterval(),
5917  td.getTransposeKeys(), td.getTransposeChordNames(), td.useDoubleSharpsFlats());
5918 
5919  if (noSelection)
5920  cs->deselectAll();
5921  }
5922 
5923 //---------------------------------------------------------
5924 // realizeChordSymbols
5925 /// Realize selected chord symbols into notes on the staff.
5926 /// Display dialog to offer overrides to default behavior
5927 //---------------------------------------------------------
5928 
5929 void MuseScore::realizeChordSymbols()
5930  {
5931  if (!cs)
5932  return;
5933  if (!cs->selection().isList()) {
5934  QErrorMessage err;
5935  err.showMessage(tr("Invalid selection. Cannot realize chord symbol"));
5936  err.exec();
5937  return;
5938  }
5939  QList<Harmony*> hlist;
5940  for (Element* e : cs->selection().elements()) {
5941  if (e->isHarmony())
5942  hlist << toHarmony(e);
5943  }
5944 
5945  RealizeHarmonyDialog dialog;
5946  if (!hlist.empty()) {
5947  dialog.setChordList(hlist);
5948  }
5949  else {
5950  QErrorMessage err;
5951  err.showMessage(tr("No chord symbol selected. Cannot realize chord symbol"));
5952  err.exec();
5953  return;
5954  }
5955 
5956  if (dialog.exec()) { //realize the chord symbols onto the track
5957  cs->startCmd();
5958  cs->cmdRealizeChordSymbols(dialog.getLiteral(),
5959  dialog.optionsOverride() ? Voicing(dialog.getVoicing()) : Voicing::INVALID,
5960  dialog.optionsOverride() ? HDuration(dialog.getDuration()) : HDuration::INVALID);
5961  cs->endCmd();
5962  }
5963  }
5964 
5965 
5966 //---------------------------------------------------------
5967 // cmd
5968 //---------------------------------------------------------
5969 
5970 void MuseScore::cmd(QAction* a)
5971  {
5972  if (inChordEditor) // HACK
5973  return;
5974 
5975  MScore::setError(MS_NO_ERROR);
5976 
5977  QString cmdn(a->data().toString());
5978 
5979  if (MScore::debugMode)
5980  qDebug("MuseScore::cmd <%s>", qPrintable(cmdn));
5981 
5982  const Shortcut* sc = Shortcut::getShortcut(cmdn.toLatin1().data());
5983  if (sc == 0) {
5984  qDebug("MuseScore::cmd(): unknown action <%s>", qPrintable(cmdn));
5985  return;
5986  }
5987  if (cs && (sc->state() & _sstate) == 0) {
5988  qDebug("invalid state %04x %04x", sc->state(), _sstate);
5989  QMessageBox::warning(0,
5990  tr("Invalid Command"),
5991  tr("Command %1 not valid in current state").arg(cmdn));
5992  return;
5993  }
5994  if (cmdn == "toggle-palette") {
5995  showPalette(a->isChecked());
5996  if (a->isChecked())
5997  paletteWidget->activateSearchBox();
5998  else if (cv)
5999  cv->setFocus();
6000  return;
6001  }
6002  if (cmdn == "palette-search") {
6003  showPalette(true);
6004  if (paletteWidget)
6005  paletteWidget->activateSearchBox();
6006  return;
6007  }
6008  if (cmdn == "apply-current-palette-element") {
6009  if (paletteWidget)
6010  paletteWidget->applyCurrentPaletteElement();
6011  return;
6012  }
6013  if (cmdn == "repeat-cmd") {
6014  a = lastCmd;
6015  sc = lastShortcut;
6016  if (a == 0)
6017  return;
6018  cmdn = a->data().toString();
6019  }
6020  else {
6021  lastCmd = a;
6022  lastShortcut = sc;
6023  }
6024 
6025  if (sc->needsScore() && ! cs) {
6026  qDebug("no score");
6027  return;
6028  }
6029  if (sc->isCmd()) {
6030  if (!cv->editMode())
6031  cs->startCmd();
6032  }
6033  cmd(a, cmdn);
6034  if (lastShortcut->isCmd())
6035  cs->endCmd();
6036  else if (!lastShortcut->isUndoRedo()) // undoRedo() calls endCmd() itself
6037  endCmd();
6038  TourHandler::startTour(cmdn);
6039  }
6040 
6041 //---------------------------------------------------------
6042 // endCmd
6043 // Called after every command action (including every
6044 // mouse action).
6045 // Updates the UI after a possible score change.
6046 //---------------------------------------------------------
6047 
6048 void MuseScore::endCmd(bool undoRedo)
6049  {
6050 #ifdef SCRIPT_INTERFACE
6051  getPluginEngine()->beginEndCmd(this, undoRedo);
6052 #endif
6053  if (timeline())
6054  timeline()->updateGridFromCmdState();
6055  if (MScore::_error != MS_NO_ERROR)
6056  showError();
6057  if (cs) {
6058  setPos(cs->inputState().tick());
6059  updateInputState(cs);
6060  updateUndoRedo();
6061  dirtyChanged(cs);
6062  scoreCmpTool->updateDiff();
6063  Element* e = cs->selection().element();
6064 
6065  // For multiple notes selected check if they all have same pitch and tuning
6066  bool samePitch = true;
6067  int pitch = -1;
6068  float tuning = 0;
6069  for (Element* ee : cs->selection().elements()) {
6070  if (!ee->isNote()) {
6071  samePitch = false;
6072  break;
6073  }
6074  Note* note = toNote(ee);
6075  if (pitch == -1) {
6076  pitch = note->ppitch();
6077  tuning = note->tuning();
6078  }
6079  else if (note->ppitch() != pitch || fabs(tuning - note->tuning()) > 0.01) {
6080  samePitch = false;
6081  break;
6082  }
6083  }
6084  if (samePitch && pitch >= 0)
6085  e = cs->selection().elements()[0];
6086 
6087  NoteEntryMethod entryMethod = cs->noteEntryMethod();
6088  if (e && (cs->playNote() || cs->playChord())
6089  && entryMethod != NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_AUTO
6090  && entryMethod != NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_MANUAL) {
6091  if (cs->playChord() && preferences.getBool(PREF_SCORE_CHORD_PLAYONADDNOTE) && e->type() == ElementType::NOTE)
6092  play(static_cast<Note*>(e)->chord());
6093  else
6094  play(e);
6095  cs->setPlayNote(false);
6096  cs->setPlayChord(false);
6097  }
6098  MasterScore* ms = cs->masterScore();
6099  if (ms->excerptsChanged()) {
6100  if (tab1) {
6101  tab1->blockSignals(ctab != tab1);
6102  tab1->updateExcerpts();
6103  tab1->blockSignals(false);
6104  }
6105  if (tab2) {
6106  tab2->blockSignals(ctab != tab2);
6107  tab2->updateExcerpts();
6108  tab2->blockSignals(false);
6109  }
6110  ms->setExcerptsChanged(false);
6111  }
6112  if (ms->instrumentsChanged()) {
6113  if (!noSeq && (seq && seq->isRunning()))
6114  seq->initInstruments();
6115  instrumentChanged(); // update mixer
6116  ms->setInstrumentsChanged(false);
6117  }
6118  if (cs->selectionChanged()) {
6119  cs->setSelectionChanged(false);
6120  SelState ss = cs->selection().state();
6121  selectionChanged(ss);
6122  }
6123 
6124  if (cv)
6125  cv->moveViewportToLastEdit();
6126 
6127  getAction("concert-pitch")->setChecked(cs->styleB(Sid::concertPitch));
6128 
6129  if (e == 0 && cs->noteEntryMode())
6130  e = cs->inputState().cr();
6131  updateViewModeCombo();
6132  ScoreAccessibility::instance()->updateAccessibilityInfo();
6133  }
6134  else {
6135  selectionChanged(SelState::NONE);
6136  }
6137  updateInspector();
6138  updatePaletteBeamMode();
6139 #ifdef SCRIPT_INTERFACE
6140  getPluginEngine()->endEndCmd(this);
6141 #endif
6142  }
6143 
6144 //---------------------------------------------------------
6145 // updateUndoRedo
6146 //---------------------------------------------------------
6147 
6148 void MuseScore::updateUndoRedo()
6149  {
6150  QAction* a = getAction("undo");
6151  a->setEnabled(cs ? cs->undoStack()->canUndo() : false);
6152  a = getAction("redo");
6153  a->setEnabled(cs ? cs->undoStack()->canRedo() : false);
6154  }

6186 //---------------------------------------------------------
6187 // createScoreTab
6188 //---------------------------------------------------------
6189 
6190 ScoreTab* MuseScore::createScoreTab()
6191  {
6192  ScoreTab* tab = new ScoreTab(&scoreList, this);
6193  tab->setSizePolicy(QSizePolicy::Expanding, QSizePolicy::Expanding);
6194  connect(tab, SIGNAL(currentScoreViewChanged(ScoreView*)), SLOT(setCurrentScoreView(ScoreView*)));
6195  connect(tab, SIGNAL(tabCloseRequested(int)), SLOT(removeTab(int)));
6196  connect(tab, SIGNAL(actionTriggered(QAction*)), SLOT(cmd(QAction*)));
6197  return tab;
6198  }

6204 void MuseScore::cmd(QAction* a, const QString& cmd)
6205  {
6206  if (ScriptRecorder* rec = getScriptRecorder())

6208 
6209  if (cmd == "instruments")
6210  editInstrumentList();

6212  if (cs) {
6213  Fraction tick = loop() ? cs->loopInTick() : Fraction(0,1);
6214  seq->seek(tick.ticks());
6215  if (cv) {
6216  Measure* m = cs->tick2measureMM(tick);
6217  if (m)
6218  cv->gotoMeasure(m);
6219  }
6220  if (playPanel)
6221  playPanel->heartBeat(0, 0, 0);
6222  }
6223  }
6224  else if (cmd == "play-next-measure")
6225  seq->nextMeasure();
6226  else if (cmd == "play-next-chord")
6227  seq->nextChord();
6228  else if (cmd == "play-prev-measure")
6229  seq->prevMeasure();
6230  else if (cmd == "play-prev-chord")
6231  seq->prevChord();
6232  else if (cmd == "seek-begin")
6233  seq->rewindStart();
6234  else if (cmd == "seek-end")
6235  seq->seekEnd();

6245  saveFile();
6246  else if (cmd == "file-save-as")
6247  saveAs(cs, false);

6506  _textTools->toggleItalic();
6507  }
6508  else if (cmd == "text-u") {
6509  if (_textTools)
6510  _textTools->toggleUnderline();
6511  }
6512  else if (cmd == "edit-toolbars")
6513  showToolbarEditor();
6514  else if (cmd == "viewmode") {
6515  if (cs) {
6516  if (cs->layoutMode() == LayoutMode::PAGE)
6517  switchLayoutMode(LayoutMode::LINE);
6518  else
6519  switchLayoutMode(LayoutMode::PAGE);
6520  }
6521  }
6522  else if (cmd == "show-tours")
6523  preferences.setPreference(PREF_UI_APP_STARTUP_SHOWTOURS, a->isChecked());
6524  else if (cmd == "reset-tours")
6525  tourHandler()->resetCompletedTours();
6526  else if (cmd == "report-bug")
6527  reportBug("panel");
6528  else if (cmd == "leave-feedback")
6529  leaveFeedback("panel");
6530 #ifndef NDEBUG
6531  else if (cmd == "no-horizontal-stretch") {
6532  MScore::noHorizontalStretch = a->isChecked();
6533  if (cs) {
6534  cs->setLayoutAll();
6535  cs->update();
6536  }
6537  }
6538  else if (cmd == "no-vertical-stretch") {
6539  MScore::noVerticalStretch = a->isChecked();
6540  if (cs) {
6541  cs->setLayoutAll();
6542  cs->update();
6543  }
6544  }
6545  else if (cmd == "show-segment-shapes") {
6546  MScore::showSegmentShapes = a->isChecked();
6547  if (cs) {
6548  cs->setLayoutAll();
6549  cs->update();
6550  }
6551  }
6552  else if (cmd == "show-skylines") {
6553  MScore::showSkylines = a->isChecked();
6554  if (cs) {
6555  cs->setLayoutAll();
6556  cs->update();
6557  }
6558  }
6559  else if (cmd == "show-bounding-rect") {
6560  MScore::showBoundingRect = a->isChecked();
6561  if (cs) {
6562  cs->setLayoutAll();
6563  cs->update();
6564  }
6565  }
6566  else if (cmd == "show-system-bounding-rect") {
6567  MScore::showSystemBoundingRect = a->isChecked();
6568  if (cs) {
6569  cs->setLayoutAll();
6570  cs->update();
6571  }
6572  }
6573  else if (cmd == "show-corrupted-measures") {
6574  MScore::showCorruptedMeasures = a->isChecked();
6575  if (cs) {
6576  cs->setLayoutAll();
6577  cs->update();
6578  }
6579  }
6580  else if (cmd == "qml-reload-source") {
6581  const QList<QmlDockWidget*> qmlWidgets = findChildren<QmlDockWidget*>();
6582 
6583  const QString oldPrefix = QmlDockWidget::qmlSourcePrefix();
6584  useSourceQmlFiles = true;
6585  const QString newPrefix = QmlDockWidget::qmlSourcePrefix();
6586 
6587  getQmlUiEngine()->clearComponentCache();
6588 
6589  for (QmlDockWidget* w : qmlWidgets) {
6590  const QString urlString = w->source().toString().replace(oldPrefix, newPrefix);
6591  w->setSource(QUrl(urlString));
6592  }
6593  }
6594 #endif
6595  else {
6596  if (cv) {
6597  //isAncestorOf is called to see if a widget from inspector has focus
6598  //if so, the focus doesn't get shifted to the score, unless escape is
6599  //pressed, or the user clicks in the score
6600  if (!inspector()->isAncestorOf(qApp->focusWidget()) || cmd == "escape")
6601  cv->setFocus();
6602  cv->cmd(a);
6603  }
6604  else
6605  qDebug("2:unknown cmd <%s>", qPrintable(cmd));
6606  }
6607  if (debugger)
6608  debugger->reloadClicked();
6609  }

6756 //---------------------------------------------------------
6757 // changeScore
6758 // switch current score
6759 // step = 1 switch to next score
6760 // step = -1 switch to previous score
6761 //---------------------------------------------------------
6762 
6763 void MuseScore::changeScore(int step)
6764  {
6765  int index = tab1->currentIndex();
6766  int n = tab1->count();
6767  if (n == 1)
6768  return;
6769  index += step;
6770  if (index >= n)
6771  index = 0;
6772  if (index < 0)
6773  index = n - 1;
6774  setCurrentScoreView(index);
6775  }

6785  return;

6787  }
6788 
6789 void MuseScore::switchLayoutMode(LayoutMode mode)
6790  {
6791  // find a measure to use as reference, if possible
6792  QRectF view = cv->toLogical(QRect(0.0, 0.0, width(), height()));
6793  Measure* m = cs->firstMeasureMM();
6794  while (m && !view.intersects(m->canvasBoundingRect()))
6795  m = m->nextMeasureMM();
6796 
6797  cv->loopUpdate(getAction("loop")->isChecked());
6798 
6799  if (mode != cs->layoutMode()) {
6800  cs->setLayoutMode(mode);
6801  cs->doLayout();
6802  }
6803 
6804  // adjustCanvasPosition often tries to preserve Y position
6805  // but this doesn't make sense when switching modes
6806  // also, better positioning is usually achieved if you start from the top
6807  // and there is really no better place to position canvas if we were all the way off page previously
6808  cv->pageTop();
6809  if (m && m != cs->firstMeasureMM())
6810  cv->adjustCanvasPosition(m, false);
6811  if (cv->noteEntryMode())
6812  cv->moveCursor();
6813  }

6929 void MuseScore::updateWindowTitle(Score* score)

6952 //---------------------------------------------------------
6953 // recentScores
6954 // return a list of recent scores
6955 // omit loaded scores
6956 //---------------------------------------------------------
6957 
6958 QFileInfoList MuseScore::recentScores() const
6959  {
6960  QFileInfoList fil;
6961  for (const QString& s : _recentScores) {
6962  if (s.isEmpty())
6963  continue;
6964  QFileInfo fi(s);
6965  bool alreadyLoaded = false;
6966  QString fp = fi.canonicalFilePath();
6967  for (Score* sc : mscore->scores()) {
6968  if ((sc->masterScore()->fileInfo()->canonicalFilePath() == fp) || (sc->importedFilePath() == fp)) {
6969  alreadyLoaded = true;
6970  break;
6971  }
6972  }
6973  if (!alreadyLoaded && fi.exists())
6974  fil.append(fi);
6975  }
6976  return fil;
6977  }

7025 //---------------------------------------------------------
7026 // canSaveMp3
7027 //---------------------------------------------------------
7028 
7029 bool MuseScore::canSaveMp3()
7030  {
7031 #ifndef USE_LAME
7032  return false;
7033 #else
7034  MP3Exporter exporter;
7035  if (!exporter.loadLibrary(MP3Exporter::AskUser::NO)) {
7036  qDebug("Could not open MP3 encoding library!");
7037  return false;
7038  }
7039 
7040  if (!exporter.validLibraryLoaded()) {
7041  qDebug("Not a valid or supported MP3 encoding library!");
7042  return false;
7043  }
7044  return true;
7045 #endif
7046  }
7047 
7048 //---------------------------------------------------------
7049 // saveMp3
7050 //---------------------------------------------------------
7051 
7052 bool MuseScore::saveMp3(Score* score, const QString& name)
7053  {
7054  QFile file(name);
7055  if (!file.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly)) {
7056  if (!MScore::noGui) {
7057  QMessageBox::warning(0,
7058  tr("Encoding Error"),
7059  tr("Unable to open target file for writing"),
7060  QString(), QString());
7061  }
7062  return false;
7063  }
7064  bool wasCanceled = false;
7065  bool res = saveMp3(score, &file, wasCanceled);
7066  file.close();
7067  if (wasCanceled || !res)
7068  file.remove();
7069  return res;
7070  }
7071 
7072 bool MuseScore::saveMp3(Score* score, QIODevice* device, bool& wasCanceled)
7073  {
7074 #ifndef USE_LAME
7075  Q_UNUSED(score);
7076  Q_UNUSED(device);
7077  Q_UNUSED(wasCanceled);
7078  return false;
7079 #else
7080  EventMap events;
7081  // In non-GUI mode current synthesizer settings won't
7082  // allow single note dynamics. See issue #289947.
7083  const bool useCurrentSynthesizerState = !MScore::noGui;
7084 
7085  if (useCurrentSynthesizerState) {
7086  score->renderMidi(&events, synthesizerState());
7087  if (events.empty())
7088  return false;
7089  }
7090 
7091  MP3Exporter exporter;
7092  if (!exporter.loadLibrary(MP3Exporter::AskUser::MAYBE)) {
7093  QSettings set;
7094  set.setValue("/Export/lameMP3LibPath", "");
7095  if(!MScore::noGui)
7096  QMessageBox::warning(0,
7097  tr("Error Opening LAME library"),
7098  tr("Could not open MP3 encoding library!"),
7099  QString(), QString());
7100  qDebug("Could not open MP3 encoding library!");
7101  return false;
7102  }
7103 
7104  if (!exporter.validLibraryLoaded()) {
7105  QSettings set;
7106  set.setValue("/Export/lameMP3LibPath", "");
7107  if(!MScore::noGui)
7108  QMessageBox::warning(0,
7109  tr("Error Opening LAME library"),
7110  tr("Not a valid or supported MP3 encoding library!"),
7111  QString(), QString());
7112  qDebug("Not a valid or supported MP3 encoding library!");
7113  return false;
7114  }
7115 
7116  // Retrieve preferences
7117 // int highrate = 48000;
7118 // int lowrate = 8000;
7119 // int bitrate = 64;
7120 // int brate = 128;
7121 // int rmode = MODE_CBR;
7122 // int vmode = ROUTINE_FAST;
7123 // int cmode = CHANNEL_STEREO;
7124 
7125  int channels = 2;
7126 
7127  int oldSampleRate = MScore::sampleRate;
7128  int sampleRate = preferences.getInt(PREF_EXPORT_AUDIO_SAMPLERATE);
7129  exporter.setBitrate(preferences.getInt(PREF_EXPORT_MP3_BITRATE));
7130 
7131  int inSamples = exporter.initializeStream(channels, sampleRate);
7132  if (inSamples < 0) {
7133  if (!MScore::noGui) {
7134  QMessageBox::warning(0, tr("Encoding Error"),
7135  tr("Unable to initialize MP3 stream"),
7136  QString(), QString());
7137  }
7138  qDebug("Unable to initialize MP3 stream");
7139  MScore::sampleRate = oldSampleRate;
7140  return false;
7141  }
7142 
7143  int bufferSize = exporter.getOutBufferSize();
7144  uchar* bufferOut = new uchar[bufferSize];
7145  MasterSynthesizer* synth = synthesizerFactory();
7146  synth->init();
7147  synth->setSampleRate(sampleRate);
7148 
7149  const SynthesizerState state = useCurrentSynthesizerState ? mscore->synthesizerState() : score->synthesizerState();
7150  const bool setStateOk = synth->setState(state);
7151 
7152  if (!setStateOk || !synth->hasSoundFontsLoaded()) {
7153  synth->init(); // re-initialize master synthesizer with default settings
7154  synth->setSampleRate(sampleRate);
7155  }
7156 
7157  MScore::sampleRate = sampleRate;
7158 
7159  if (!useCurrentSynthesizerState) {
7160  score->masterScore()->rebuildAndUpdateExpressive(synth->synthesizer("Fluid"));
7161  score->renderMidi(&events, score->synthesizerState());
7162  if (synti)
7163  score->masterScore()->rebuildAndUpdateExpressive(synti->synthesizer("Fluid"));
7164 
7165  if (events.empty())
7166  return false;
7167  }
7168 
7169  QProgressDialog progress(this);
7170  progress.setWindowFlags(Qt::WindowFlags(Qt::Dialog | Qt::FramelessWindowHint | Qt::WindowTitleHint));
7171  progress.setWindowModality(Qt::ApplicationModal);
7172  //progress.setCancelButton(0);
7173  progress.setCancelButtonText(tr("Cancel"));
7174  progress.setLabelText(tr("Exporting…"));
7175  if (!MScore::noGui)
7176  progress.show();
7177 
7178  static const int FRAMES = 512;
7179  float bufferL[FRAMES];
7180  float bufferR[FRAMES];
7181 
7182  float peak = 0.0;
7183  double gain = 1.0;
7184  EventMap::const_iterator endPos = events.cend();
7185  --endPos;
7186  const int et = (score->utick2utime(endPos->first) + 1) * MScore::sampleRate;
7187  const int maxEndTime = (score->utick2utime(endPos->first) + 3) * MScore::sampleRate;
7188  progress.setRange(0, et);
7189 
7190  for (int pass = 0; pass < 2; ++pass) {
7191  EventMap::const_iterator playPos;
7192  playPos = events.cbegin();
7193  synth->allSoundsOff(-1);
7194 
7195  //
7196  // init instruments
7197  //
7198  for (Part* part : score->parts()) {
7199  const InstrumentList* il = part->instruments();
7200  for (auto i = il->begin(); i!= il->end(); i++) {
7201  for (const Channel* channel : i->second->channel()) {
7202  const Channel* a = score->masterScore()->playbackChannel(channel);
7203  for (MidiCoreEvent e : a->initList()) {
7204  if (e.type() == ME_INVALID)
7205  continue;
7206  e.setChannel(a->channel());
7207  int syntiIdx= synth->index(score->masterScore()->midiMapping(a->channel())->articulation()->synti());
7208  synth->play(e, syntiIdx);
7209  }
7210  }
7211  }
7212  }
7213 
7214  int playTime = 0.0;
7215 
7216  for (;;) {
7217  unsigned frames = FRAMES;
7218  float max = 0;
7219  //
7220  // collect events for one segment
7221  //
7222  memset(bufferL, 0, sizeof(float) * FRAMES);
7223  memset(bufferR, 0, sizeof(float) * FRAMES);
7224  double endTime = playTime + frames;
7225 
7226  float* l = bufferL;
7227  float* r = bufferR;
7228 
7229  for (; playPos != events.cend(); ++playPos) {
7230  double f = score->utick2utime(playPos->first) * MScore::sampleRate;
7231  if (f >= endTime)
7232  break;
7233  int n = f - playTime;
7234  if (n) {
7235 #if (!defined (_MSCVER) && !defined (_MSC_VER))
7236  float bu[n * 2];
7237  memset(bu, 0, sizeof(float) * 2 * n);
7238 #else
7239  // MSVC does not support VLA. Replace with std::vector. If profiling determines that the
7240  // heap allocation is slow, an optimization might be used.
7241  std::vector<float> vBu(n * 2, 0); // Default initialized, memset() not required.
7242  float* bu = vBu.data();
7243 #endif
7244 
7245  synth->process(n, bu);
7246  float* sp = bu;
7247  for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
7248  *l++ = *sp++;
7249  *r++ = *sp++;
7250  }
7251  playTime += n;
7252  frames -= n;
7253  }
7254  const NPlayEvent& e = playPos->second;
7255  if (!(!e.velo() && e.discard()) && e.isChannelEvent()) {
7256  int channelIdx = e.channel();
7257  Channel* c = score->masterScore()->midiMapping(channelIdx)->articulation();
7258  if (!c->mute()) {
7259  synth->play(e, synth->index(c->synti()));
7260  }
7261  }
7262  }
7263  if (frames) {
7264 #if (!defined (_MSCVER) && !defined (_MSC_VER))
7265  float bu[frames * 2];
7266  memset(bu, 0, sizeof(float) * 2 * frames);
7267 #else
7268  // MSVC does not support VLA. Replace with std::vector. If profiling determines that the
7269  // heap allocation is slow, an optimization might be used.
7270  std::vector<float> vBu(frames * 2, 0); // Default initialized, memset() not required.
7271  float* bu = vBu.data();
7272 #endif
7273  synth->process(frames, bu);
7274  float* sp = bu;
7275  for (unsigned i = 0; i < frames; ++i) {
7276  *l++ = *sp++;
7277  *r++ = *sp++;
7278  }
7279  playTime += frames;
7280  }
7281 
7282  if (pass == 1) {
7283  for (int i = 0; i < FRAMES; ++i) {
7284  max = qMax(max, qAbs(bufferL[i]));
7285  max = qMax(max, qAbs(bufferR[i]));
7286  bufferL[i] *= gain;
7287  bufferR[i] *= gain;
7288  }
7289  long bytes;
7290  if (FRAMES < inSamples)
7291  bytes = exporter.encodeRemainder(bufferL, bufferR, FRAMES , bufferOut);
7292  else
7293  bytes = exporter.encodeBuffer(bufferL, bufferR, bufferOut);
7294  if (bytes < 0) {
7295  if (MScore::noGui)
7296  qDebug("exportmp3: error from encoder: %ld", bytes);
7297  else
7298  QMessageBox::warning(0,
7299  tr("Encoding Error"),
7300  tr("Error %1 returned from MP3 encoder").arg(bytes),
7301  QString(), QString());
7302  break;
7303  }
7304  else
7305  device->write((char*)bufferOut, bytes);
7306  }
7307  else {
7308  for (int i = 0; i < FRAMES; ++i) {
7309  max = qMax(max, qAbs(bufferL[i]));
7310  max = qMax(max, qAbs(bufferR[i]));
7311  peak = qMax(peak, qAbs(bufferL[i]));
7312  peak = qMax(peak, qAbs(bufferR[i]));
7313  }
7314  }
7315  playTime = endTime;
7316  if (!MScore::noGui) {
7317  if (progress.wasCanceled())
7318  break;
7319  progress.setValue((pass * et + playTime) / 2);
7320  qApp->processEvents();
7321  }
7322  if (playTime >= et)
7323  synth->allNotesOff(-1);
7324  // create sound until the sound decays
7325  if (playTime >= et && max * peak < 0.000001)
7326  break;
7327  // hard limit
7328  if (playTime > maxEndTime)
7329  break;
7330  }
7331  if (progress.wasCanceled())
7332  break;
7333  if (pass == 0 && peak == 0.0) {
7334  qDebug("song is empty");
7335  break;
7336  }
7337  gain = 0.99 / peak;
7338  }
7339 
7340  long bytes = exporter.finishStream(bufferOut);
7341  if (bytes > 0L)
7342  device->write((char*)bufferOut, bytes);
7343  wasCanceled = progress.wasCanceled();
7344  progress.close();
7345  delete synth;
7346  delete[] bufferOut;
7347  MScore::sampleRate = oldSampleRate;
7348  return true;
7349 #endif
7350  }

7352 #ifndef TELEMETRY_DISABLED
7353 
7354 //---------------------------------------------------------
7355 // tryToRequestTelemetryPermission
7356 //---------------------------------------------------------
7357 
7358 void tryToRequestTelemetryPermission()
7359  {
7360  static const QString telemetryVersion = "3.4.1";
7361  QString accessRequestedAtVersion = preferences.getString(PREF_APP_STARTUP_TELEMETRY_ACCESS_REQUESTED);
7362 
7363  if (accessRequestedAtVersion == telemetryVersion)
7364  return;
7365 
7366  // Disable telemetry until the permission is explicitly confirmed by user
7367  preferences.setPreference(PREF_APP_TELEMETRY_ALLOWED, false);
7368 
7369  if (MScore::noGui)
7370  return;
7371 
7372  QEventLoop eventLoop;
7373 
7374  TelemetryPermissionDialog *requestDialog = new TelemetryPermissionDialog(mscore->getQmlUiEngine());
7375  QObject::connect(requestDialog, &TelemetryPermissionDialog::closeRequested, [&eventLoop] () {
7376  eventLoop.quit();
7377  });
7378 
7379  requestDialog->show();
7380  eventLoop.exec();
7381  requestDialog->deleteLater();
7382 
7383  preferences.setPreference(PREF_APP_STARTUP_TELEMETRY_ACCESS_REQUESTED, telemetryVersion);
7384  }
7385 #endif

7387 //---------------------------------------------------------
7388 // updateUiStyleAndTheme
7389 //---------------------------------------------------------
7390 
7391 void MuseScore::updateUiStyleAndTheme()
7392  {
7393  // set UI Theme
7394  QApplication::setStyle(QStyleFactory::create("Fusion"));
7395 
7396 #ifdef Q_OS_MAC
7397  // On Mac, update the color of the window title bars
7398  CocoaBridge::setWindowAppearanceIsDark(preferences.isThemeDark());
7399 #endif
7400 
7401 #if defined(WIN_PORTABLE)
7402  QString wd = QDir::cleanPath(QString("%1/../../../Data/%2").arg(QCoreApplication::applicationDirPath()).arg(QCoreApplication::applicationName()));
7403 #else
7404  QString wd = QString("%1/%2").arg(QStandardPaths::writableLocation(QStandardPaths::DocumentsLocation)).arg(QCoreApplication::applicationName());
7405 #endif
7406 
7407  // set UI Color Palette
7408  QPalette p(QApplication::palette());
7409  QString jsonPaletteFilename = preferences.isThemeDark() ? "palette_dark_fusion.json" : "palette_light_fusion.json";;
7410  QFile jsonPalette(QString(":/themes/%1").arg(jsonPaletteFilename));
7411  // read from Documents TODO: remove this
7412  if (QFile::exists(QString("%1/%2").arg(wd, "ms_palette.json")))
7413  jsonPalette.setFileName(QString("%1/%2").arg(wd, "ms_palette.json"));
7414  if (jsonPalette.open(QFile::ReadOnly | QFile::Text)) {
7415  QJsonDocument d = QJsonDocument::fromJson(jsonPalette.readAll());
7416  QJsonObject o = d.object();
7417  QMetaEnum metaEnum = QMetaEnum::fromType<QPalette::ColorRole>();
7418  for (int i = 0; i < metaEnum.keyCount(); ++i) {
7419  QJsonValue v = o.value(metaEnum.valueToKey(i));
7420  if (!v.isUndefined())
7421  p.setColor(static_cast<QPalette::ColorRole>(metaEnum.value(i)), QColor(v.toString()));
7422  }
7423  }
7424  QApplication::setPalette(p);
7425 
7426  // set UI Style
7427  QString css;
7428  QString styleFilename = preferences.isThemeDark() ? "style_dark_fusion.css" : "style_light_fusion.css";
7429  QFile fstyle(QString(":/themes/%1").arg(styleFilename));
7430  // read from Documents TODO: remove this
7431  if (QFile::exists(QString("%1/%2").arg(wd, "ms_style.css")))
7432  fstyle.setFileName(QString("%1/%2").arg(wd, "ms_style.css"));
7433  if (fstyle.open(QFile::ReadOnly | QFile::Text)) {
7434  QTextStream in(&fstyle);
7435  css = in.readAll();
7436  }
7437 
7438  css.replace("$voice1-bgcolor", MScore::selectColor[0].name(QColor::HexRgb));
7439  css.replace("$voice2-bgcolor", MScore::selectColor[1].name(QColor::HexRgb));
7440  css.replace("$voice3-bgcolor", MScore::selectColor[2].name(QColor::HexRgb));
7441  css.replace("$voice4-bgcolor", MScore::selectColor[3].name(QColor::HexRgb));
7442 
7443  if (preferences.isThemeDark()) {
7444  css.replace("$buttonHighlightDisabledOff", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_DISABLED_DARK_OFF).name().toLatin1());
7445  css.replace("$buttonHighlightDisabledOn", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_DISABLED_DARK_ON).name().toLatin1());
7446  css.replace("$buttonHighlightEnabledOff", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_ENABLED_DARK_OFF).name().toLatin1());
7447  css.replace("$buttonHighlightEnabledOn", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_ENABLED_DARK_ON).name().toLatin1());
7448  }
7449  else {
7450  css.replace("$buttonHighlightDisabledOff", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_DISABLED_LIGHT_OFF).name().toLatin1());
7451  css.replace("$buttonHighlightDisabledOn", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_DISABLED_LIGHT_ON).name().toLatin1());
7452  css.replace("$buttonHighlightEnabledOff", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_ENABLED_LIGHT_OFF).name().toLatin1());
7453  css.replace("$buttonHighlightEnabledOn", Ms::preferences.getColor(PREF_UI_BUTTON_HIGHLIGHT_COLOR_ENABLED_LIGHT_ON).name().toLatin1());
7454  }
7455 
7456  qApp->setStyleSheet(css);
7457 
7458  QString style = QString("*, QSpinBox { font: %1pt \"%2\" } ")
7459  .arg(QString::number(preferences.getDouble(PREF_UI_THEME_FONTSIZE)), preferences.getString(PREF_UI_THEME_FONTFAMILY))
7460  + qApp->styleSheet();
7461  qApp->setStyleSheet(style);
7462 
7463  genIcons();
7464  Shortcut::refreshIcons();
7465  }

7467 //---------------------------------------------------------
7468 // fullVersion
7469 /// \return Full version of MuseScore, including version
7470 /// label (e.g. 3.4.0-Beta).
7471 //---------------------------------------------------------
7472 
7473 QString MuseScore::fullVersion()
7474  {
7475  QString version(VERSION);
7476  QString versionLabel(VERSION_LABEL);
7477  versionLabel = versionLabel.replace(' ', "");
7478  if (!versionLabel.isEmpty())
7479  version.append("-").append(versionLabel);
7480  return version;
7481  }

7483 //---------------------------------------------------------
7484 // initApplication
7485 //---------------------------------------------------------
7486 
7487 MuseScoreApplication* MuseScoreApplication::initApplication(int& argc, char** argv)
7488  {
7489  revision = QString(MUSESCORE_REVISION).trimmed();
7490 
7491  const char* appName;
7492  const char* appName2;
7493  if (MuseScore::unstable()) {
7494  appName2 = "mscore-dev3";
7495  appName = "MuseScore3Development";
7496  }
7497  else {
7498  appName2 = "mscore3";
7499  appName = "MuseScore3";
7500  }
7501 
7502  //! NOTE Disable cache for all platforms
7503  //! Enabled qml cache on MacOS BigSur on ARM leads to a crash at the start
7504  //! There were also crash problems on some Linux platforms when upgrading
7505  //! In general, the Qml cache doesn't really matter.
7506  //! Therefore, it is better to turn it off.
7507  qputenv("QML_DISABLE_DISK_CACHE", "true");
7508 
7509  MuseScoreApplication* app = new MuseScoreApplication(appName2, argc, argv);
7510  QCoreApplication::setApplicationName(appName);
7511 
7512  QCoreApplication::setOrganizationName("MuseScore");
7513  QCoreApplication::setOrganizationDomain("musescore.org");
7514  QCoreApplication::setApplicationVersion(MuseScore::fullVersion());
7515 
7516 #ifdef BUILD_CRASH_REPORTER
7517  {
7518  static_assert(sizeof(CRASHREPORTER_EXECUTABLE) > 1,
7519  "CRASHREPORTER_EXECUTABLE should be defined to build with crash reporter"
7520  );
7521  CrashReporter::Handler* crashHandler = new CrashReporter::Handler(QDir::tempPath(), true, CRASHREPORTER_EXECUTABLE);
7522  QObject::connect(app, &QCoreApplication::aboutToQuit, [crashHandler]() { delete crashHandler; });
7523  }
7524 #endif
7525 
7526  return app;
7527  }

7533 bool MuseScoreApplication::setCustomConfigFolder(const QString& path)
7534  {
7535  const QFileInfo pinfo(path);
7536 
7537  if (pinfo.exists() && pinfo.isDir()) {
7538  QSettings::setPath(QSettings::IniFormat, QSettings::UserScope, path);
7539  QSettings::setPath(QSettings::IniFormat, QSettings::SystemScope, path);
7540  dataPath = path;
7541  return true;
7542  }
7543 
7544  return false;
7545  }
