7566  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"n", "new-score"}, "Start with new score"));
7567  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"I", "dump-midi-in"}, "Dump midi input"));
7568  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"O", "dump-midi-out"}, "Dump midi output"));
7569  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"o", "export-to"}, "Export to 'file'. Format depends on file's extension", "file"));
7570  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"r", "image-resolution"}, "Use with '-o <file>.png'. Set output resolution for image export", "DPI"));
7571  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"T", "trim-image"}, "Use with '-o <file>.png' and '-o <file.svg>'. Trim exported image with specified margin (in pixels)", "margin"));
7572  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"x", "gui-scaling"}, "Set scaling factor for GUI elements", "factor"));
7573  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"D", "monitor-resolution"}, "Specify monitor resolution", "DPI"));
7574  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"S", "style"}, "Load style file", "style"));
7575  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"p", "plugin"}, "Execute named plugin", "name"));
7576  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "template-mode", "Save template mode, no page size")); // and no platform and creationDate tags
7577  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"F", "factory-settings"}, "Use factory settings")); // this includes -R, --revert-settimngs
7578  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"R", "revert-settings"}, "Revert to factory settings, but keep default preferences"));
7579  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"i", "load-icons"}, "Load icons from INSTALLPATH/icons"));
7580  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"j", "job"}, "Process a conversion job", "file"));
7581  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"e", "experimental"}, "Enable experimental features"));
7582  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"c", "config-folder"}, "Override configuration and settings folder", "dir"));
7583  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"t", "test-mode"}, "Set test mode flag for all files")); // this includes --template-mode
7584  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "run-test-script", "Run script tests listed in the command line arguments"));
7585  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"M", "midi-operations"}, "Specify MIDI import operations file", "file"));
7586  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"w", "no-webview"}, "No web view in start center"));
7587  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"P", "export-score-parts"}, "Use with '-o <file>.pdf', export score and parts"));
7588  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "no-fallback-font", "Don't use a fallback musical font"));
7589  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"f", "force"}, "Use with '-o <file>', ignore warnings reg. score being corrupted or from wrong version"));
7590  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"b", "bitrate"}, "Use with '-o <file>.mp3', sets bitrate, in kbps", "bitrate"));
7591  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption({"E", "install-extension"}, "Install an extension, load soundfont as default unless -e is passed too", "extension file"));
7592  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "save-online", "Upload score(s) to their source URL. Replaces existing online score(s)."));
7593  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-media", "Export all media (excepting mp3) for a given score in a single JSON file and print it to stdout"));
7594  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "highlight-config", "Set highlight to svg, generated from a given score", "highlight-config"));
7595  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-meta", "Export score metadata to JSON document and print it to stdout"));
7596  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-mp3", "Generate mp3 for the given score and export the data to a single JSON file, print it to stdout"));
7597  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-parts", "Generate parts data for the given score and save them to separate mscz files"));
7598  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-parts-pdf", "Generate parts data for the given score and export the data to a single JSON file, print it to stdout"));
7599  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "score-transpose", "Transpose the given score and export the data to a single JSON file, print it to stdout", "options"));
7600  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "source-update", "Update the source in the given score"));
7601  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "raw-diff", "Print a raw diff for the given scores"));
7602  parser.addOption(QCommandLineOption( "diff", "Print a diff for the given scores"));
7603 
7604  parser.addPositionalArgument("scorefiles", "The files to open", "[scorefile...]");
7605 
7606  parser.process(QCoreApplication::arguments());
7607 
7608  //if (parser.isSet("v")) parser.showVersion(); // a) needs Qt >= 5.4 , b) instead we use addVersionOption()
7609  if (parser.isSet("long-version")) {
7610  printVersion("MuseScore");
7611  parseResult.exit = true;
7612  return parseResult;
7613  }
7614  MScore::debugMode = parser.isSet("d");
7615  MScore::noHorizontalStretch = MScore::noVerticalStretch = parser.isSet("L");
7616  noSeq = parser.isSet("s");
7617  noMidi = parser.isSet("m");
7618  if (parser.isSet("a")) {
7619  audioDriver = parser.value("a");
7620  if (audioDriver.isEmpty())
7621  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7622  }
7623  startWithNewScore = parser.isSet("n");
7624  externalIcons = parser.isSet("i");
7625  midiInputTrace = parser.isSet("I");
7626  midiOutputTrace = parser.isSet("O");
7627  MScore::useFallbackFont = !parser.isSet("no-fallback-font");
7628 
7629  if ((converterMode = parser.isSet("o"))) {
7630  MScore::noGui = true;
7631  outFileName = parser.value("o");
7632  if (outFileName.isEmpty())
7633  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7634  }
7635  if ((processJob = parser.isSet("j"))) {
7636  MScore::noGui = true;
7637  converterMode = true;
7638  jsonFileName = parser.value("j");
7639  if (jsonFileName.isEmpty()) {
7640  fprintf(stderr, "json file name missing\n");
7641  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7642  }
7643  }
7644  if ((pluginMode = parser.isSet("p"))) {
7645  MScore::noGui = true;
7646  pluginName = parser.value("p");
7647  if (pluginName.isEmpty())
7648  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7649  }
7650  if (parser.isSet("E")) {
7651  MScore::noGui = true;
7652  extensionName = parser.value("E");
7653  }
7654  MScore::saveTemplateMode = parser.isSet("template-mode");
7655  if (parser.isSet("r")) {
7656  QString temp = parser.value("r");
7657  if (temp.isEmpty())
7658  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7659  bool ok = false;
7660  double res = temp.toDouble(&ok);
7661  if (ok)
7662  preferences.setTemporaryPreference(PREF_EXPORT_PNG_RESOLUTION, res);
7663  else
7664  fprintf(stderr, "PNG resolution value '%s' not recognized, using default setting from preferences instead.\n", qPrintable(temp));
7665  }
7666  if (parser.isSet("T")) {
7667  QString temp = parser.value("T");
7668  if (temp.isEmpty())
7669  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7670  bool ok = false;
7671  trimMargin = temp.toInt(&ok);
7672  if (!ok) {
7673  fprintf(stderr, "Trim margin value '%s' not recognized, so no trimming will be done.\n", qPrintable(temp));
7674  trimMargin = -1;
7675  }
7676  }
7677  if (parser.isSet("x")) {
7678  QString temp = parser.value("x");
7679  if (temp.isEmpty())
7680  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7681  bool ok = false;
7682  guiScaling = temp.toDouble(&ok);
7683  if (!ok) {
7684  fprintf(stderr, "GUI scaling value '%s' not recognized, so the values detected by Qt are taken.\n", qPrintable(temp));
7685  guiScaling = 0.0;
7686  }
7687  }
7688  if (parser.isSet("D")) {
7689  QString temp = parser.value("D");
7690  if (temp.isEmpty())
7691  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7692  bool ok = false;
7693  userDPI = temp.toDouble(&ok);
7694  if (!ok) {
7695  fprintf(stderr, "DPI value '%s' not recognized, so the values detected by Qt are taken.\n", qPrintable(temp));
7696  userDPI = 0.0;
7697  }
7698  }
7699  if (parser.isSet("S")) {
7700  styleFile = parser.value("S");
7701  if (styleFile.isEmpty())
7702  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7703  }
7704  deletePreferences = parser.isSet("F");
7705  useFactorySettings = (deletePreferences || parser.isSet("R"));
7706  enableExperimental = parser.isSet("e");
7707  if (parser.isSet("c")) {
7708  QString path = parser.value("c");
7709  if (path.isEmpty())
7710  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7711  setCustomConfigFolder(path);
7712  }
7713  MScore::testMode = parser.isSet("t");
7714  if (parser.isSet("M")) {
7715  QString temp = parser.value("M");
7716  if (temp.isEmpty())
7717  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7718  midiImportOperations.setOperationsFile(temp);
7719  }
7720  noWebView = parser.isSet("w");
7721  exportScoreParts = parser.isSet("export-score-parts");
7722  if (exportScoreParts && !converterMode)
7723  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7724  ignoreWarnings = parser.isSet("f");
7725  if (parser.isSet("b")) {
7726  QString temp = parser.value("b");
7727  if (temp.isEmpty())
7728  parser.showHelp(EXIT_FAILURE);
7729  bool ok = false;
7730  int rate = temp.toInt(&ok);
7731  if (ok)
7732  preferences.setTemporaryPreference(PREF_EXPORT_MP3_BITRATE, rate);
7733  else
7734  fprintf(stderr, "MP3 bitrate value '%s' not recognized, using default setting from preferences instead.\n", qPrintable(temp));
7735  }
7736 
7737  if (parser.isSet("save-online")) {
7738  cliSaveOnline = true;
7739  MScore::noGui = true;
7740 
7741  if (parser.positionalArguments().isEmpty()) {
7742  fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", qPrintable(tr("Must specify at least one score to save online.")));
7743  ::exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7744  }
7745  }
7746 
7747  if (parser.isSet("score-media")) {
7748  exportScoreMedia = true;
7749  MScore::noGui = true;
7750  converterMode = true;
7751 
7752  if (parser.isSet("highlight-config")) {
7753  highlightConfigPath = parser.value("highlight-config");
7754  }
7755  }
7756 
7757  if (parser.isSet("score-meta")) {
7758  exportScoreMeta = true;
7759  MScore::noGui = true;
7760  converterMode = true;
7761  }
7762 
7763  if (parser.isSet("score-mp3")) {
7764  exportScoreMp3 = true;
7765  MScore::noGui = true;
7766  converterMode = true;
7767  }
7768 
7769  if (parser.isSet("score-parts")) {
7770  saveScoreParts = true;
7771  MScore::noGui = true;
7772  converterMode = true;
7773  }
7774 
7775  if (parser.isSet("score-parts-pdf")) {
7776  exportScorePartsPdf = true;
7777  MScore::noGui = true;
7778  converterMode = true;
7779  }
7780 
7781  if (parser.isSet("score-transpose")) {
7782  exportTransposedScore = true;
7783  transposeExportOptions = parser.value("score-transpose");
7784  MScore::noGui = true;
7785  converterMode = true;
7786  }
7787 
7788  if (parser.isSet("source-update")) {
7789  MScore::noGui = true;
7790  needUpdateSource = true;
7791  }
7792 
7793  if (parser.isSet("raw-diff")) {
7794  MScore::noGui = true;
7795  rawDiffMode = true;
7796  }
7797  if (parser.isSet("diff")) {
7798  MScore::noGui = true;
7799  diffMode = true;
7800  }
7801  if (parser.isSet("run-test-script")) {
7802  if (rawDiffMode || diffMode) {
7803  fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", qPrintable(tr("--run-test-script is incompatible with --diff and --raw-diff")));
7804  ::exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7805  }
7806  MScore::noGui = true;
7807  scriptTestMode = true;
7808  }
7809 
7810  QStringList argv = parser.positionalArguments();
7811 
7812  if (app && !converterMode && !pluginMode) {
7813  if (!argv.isEmpty()) {
7814  int ok = true;
7815  for (const QString& message : argv) {
7816  QFileInfo fi(message);
7817  if (!app->sendMessage(fi.absoluteFilePath())) {
7818  ok = false;
7819  break;
7820  }
7821 
7822  }
7823  if (ok) {
7824  parseResult.exit = true;
7825  return parseResult;
7826  }
7827  }
7828  else
7829  if (app->sendMessage(QString(""))) {
7830  parseResult.exit = true;
7831  return parseResult;
7832  }
7833  }
7834  if (rawDiffMode || diffMode) {
7835  if (argv.size() != 2) {
7836  fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", qPrintable(tr("Only two scores are needed for performing a comparison")));
7837  ::exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7838  }
7839  }
7840  if (scriptTestMode && argv.empty()) {
7841  fprintf(stderr, "%s\n", qPrintable(tr("Please specify scripts to execute")));
7842  ::exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7843  }
7844 
7845  parseResult.argv = argv;
7846  return parseResult;
7847  }
7848 } // namespace Ms

7864 
7865 int runApplication(int& argc, char** av)
7866  {
7867 #ifndef NDEBUG
7868  qSetMessagePattern("%{file}:%{function}: %{message}");
7869  Ms::checkStyles();
7870 #endif
7871 
7872  QApplication::setDesktopSettingsAware(true);
7873 #ifdef Q_OS_LINUX
7874  QGuiApplication::setDesktopFileName("mscore");
7875 #endif
7876  QApplication::setAttribute(Qt::AA_UseHighDpiPixmaps);
7877  QApplication::setAttribute(Qt::AA_EnableHighDpiScaling);
7878 #if defined(QT_DEBUG) && defined(Q_OS_WIN)
7879  qInstallMessageHandler(mscoreMessageHandler);
7880 #endif
7881 
7882 #ifdef Q_OS_WIN
7883  if (!qEnvironmentVariableIsSet("QT_OPENGL_BUGLIST")) {
7884  // Set custom OpenGL buglist to work around rendering issues
7885  // on Windows 7 (#296682). This should also prevent crashes
7886  // happening for some Intel GPUs due to outdated buglist in Qt 5.9.
7887  qputenv("QT_OPENGL_BUGLIST", ":/data/win_opengl_buglist.json");
7888  }
7889 #endif
7890 
7891  qRegisterMetaTypeStreamOperators<SessionStart>("SessionStart");
7892  qRegisterMetaTypeStreamOperators<MusicxmlExportBreaks>("MusicxmlExportBreaks");
7893  qRegisterMetaTypeStreamOperators<MuseScorePreferredStyleType>("MuseScorePreferredStyleType");
7894  qRegisterMetaTypeStreamOperators<MuseScoreEffectiveStyleType>("MuseScoreEffectiveStyleType");
7895 
7896  MuseScoreApplication* app = MuseScoreApplication::initApplication(argc, av);
7897 
7898  QAccessible::installFactory(AccessibleScoreView::ScoreViewFactory);
7899  QAccessible::installFactory(AccessibleSearchBox::SearchBoxFactory);
7900  QAccessible::installFactory(Awl::AccessibleAbstractSlider::AbstractSliderFactory);
7901 
7902  initZitaResources();
7903 
7904 #ifndef Q_OS_MAC
7905  QSettings::setDefaultFormat(QSettings::IniFormat);
7906 #endif
7907 
7908  auto cmdLineParseResult = MuseScoreApplication::parseCommandLineArguments(app);
7909 
7910  if (cmdLineParseResult.exit)
7911  return 0;
7912 
7913  MuseScore::init(cmdLineParseResult.argv);
7914 
7915  if (MScore::noGui) {
7916 #ifdef Q_OS_MAC
7917  // see issue #28706: Hangup in converter mode with MusicXML source
7918  qApp->processEvents();
7919 #endif
7920  const bool ok = processNonGui(cmdLineParseResult.argv);
7921  return ok ? EXIT_SUCCESS : EXIT_FAILURE;
7922  }
7923 
7924  QDir::setCurrent(app->applicationDirPath());
7925 
7926  return qApp->exec();
7927  }

7935  if (sc)
7936  sc->showMessage(message);
7937  else
7938  qInfo("%s", qPrintable(message));
7939  }

7945 void MuseScore::init(QStringList& argv)
7946  {
7947  mscoreGlobalShare = getSharePath();
7948  iconPath = externalIcons ? mscoreGlobalShare + QString("icons/") : QString(":/data/icons/");
7949 
7950 #if defined(WIN_PORTABLE)
7951  if (dataPath.isEmpty()) {
7952  dataPath = QDir::cleanPath(QString("%1/../../../Data/settings").arg(QCoreApplication::applicationDirPath()).arg(QCoreApplication::applicationName()));
7953  QSettings::setPath(QSettings::IniFormat, QSettings::UserScope, dataPath);
7954  QSettings::setPath(QSettings::IniFormat, QSettings::SystemScope, dataPath);
7955  }
7956 #else
7957  if (dataPath.isEmpty())

7959 #endif
7960 
7961  if (useFactorySettings) {
7962  if (deletePreferences)
7963  QDir(dataPath).removeRecursively();
7964  QSettings settings;
7965  QFile::remove(settings.fileName() + ".lock"); //forcibly remove lock
7966  QFile::remove(settings.fileName());
7967  settings.clear();
7968  }
7969 
7970  // create local plugin directory
7971  // if not already there:
7972  QDir().mkpath(dataPath + "/plugins");
7973 
7974  if (MScore::debugMode)
7975  qDebug("global share: <%s>", qPrintable(mscoreGlobalShare));
7976 
7977  // Set translator before Shortcuts are initialized to get translations for all shortcuts.
7978  // Cannot use `preferences` or `localeName()` (which uses `preferences`) to retrieve
7979  // these values, as `preferences` needs to be initialized after translator is set.
7980  QString localeName;
7981  if (useFactorySettings)
7982  localeName = "system";
7983  else {

7994

7998  // initialize current page size from default printer
7999 #ifndef QT_NO_PRINTER
8000  if (!MScore::testMode && !MScore::saveTemplateMode) {
8001  QPrinter p;

8003 // qDebug("set paper size from default printer");
8004  QRectF psf = p.paperRect(QPrinter::Inch);

8006  MScore::defaultStyle().set(Sid::pageHeight, psf.height());

8008  }
8009  }
8010 #endif
8011 
8012  if (MScore::debugMode) {
8013  qDebug("DPI %f", DPI);

8015  QScreen* screen = QGuiApplication::primaryScreen();
8016  qDebug() << "Information for screen:" << screen->name();
8017  qDebug() << " Available geometry:" << screen->availableGeometry().x() << screen->availableGeometry().y() << screen->availableGeometry().width() << "x" << screen->availableGeometry().height();
8018  qDebug() << " Available size:" << screen->availableSize().width() << "x" << screen->availableSize().height();
8019  qDebug() << " Available virtual geometry:" << screen->availableVirtualGeometry().x() << screen->availableVirtualGeometry().y() << screen->availableVirtualGeometry().width() << "x" << screen->availableVirtualGeometry().height();
8020  qDebug() << " Available virtual size:" << screen->availableVirtualSize().width() << "x" << screen->availableVirtualSize().height();
8021  qDebug() << " Depth:" << screen->depth() << "bits";
8022  qDebug() << " Geometry:" << screen->geometry().x() << screen->geometry().y() << screen->geometry().width() << "x" << screen->geometry().height();
8023  qDebug() << " Logical DPI:" << screen->logicalDotsPerInch();
8024  qDebug() << " Logical DPI X:" << screen->logicalDotsPerInchX();
8025  qDebug() << " Logical DPI Y:" << screen->logicalDotsPerInchY();
8026  qDebug() << " Physical DPI:" << screen->physicalDotsPerInch();
8027  qDebug() << " Physical DPI X:" << screen->physicalDotsPerInchX();
8028  qDebug() << " Physical DPI Y:" << screen->physicalDotsPerInchY();
8029  qDebug() << " Physical size:" << screen->physicalSize().width() << "x" << screen->physicalSize().height() << "mm";
8030  qDebug() << " Refresh rate:" << screen->refreshRate() << "Hz";
8031  qDebug() << " Size:" << screen->size().width() << "x" << screen->size().height();
8032  qDebug() << " Virtual geometry:" << screen->virtualGeometry().x() << screen->virtualGeometry().y() << screen->virtualGeometry().width() << "x" << screen->virtualGeometry().height();
8033  qDebug() << " Virtual size:" << screen->virtualSize().width() << "x" << screen->virtualSize().height();
8034  }
8035 
8036  if (!MScore::testMode)

8041  sc = new MsSplashScreen();
8042  sc->show();
8043  qApp->processEvents();
8044  }
8045 
8046  // Best not to show this since the font used to display the message
8047  // isn't updated till updateUiStyleAndTheme()
8048  // showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Updating user interface and theme…"));
8049  if (!MScore::noGui) {
8050  MuseScore::updateUiStyleAndTheme();
8051  }
8052  else {
8053  genIcons(); // in GUI mode generated in updateUiStyleAndTheme()
8054  noSeq = true;
8055  }
8056 
8057  // Do not create sequencer and audio drivers if run with '-s'
8058  if (!noSeq) {
8059  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing sequencer and audio driver…"));
8060  seq = new Seq();
8061  MScore::seq = seq;
8062  Driver* driver = driverFactory(seq, audioDriver);
8063  synti = synthesizerFactory();
8064  if (driver) {
8065  MScore::sampleRate = driver->sampleRate();
8066  synti->setSampleRate(MScore::sampleRate);
8067 
8068  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Loading SoundFonts…"));
8069  synti->init();
8070 
8071  seq->setDriver(driver);
8072  }
8073  else {
8074  // Do not delete the sequencer If we can't load driver.
8075  // Allow user to select the working driver later.
8076  MScore::sampleRate = 44100; // Would be changed when user changes driver
8077  synti->setSampleRate(MScore::sampleRate);
8078  synti->init();
8079  }
8080  seq->setMasterSynthesizer(synti);
8081  }
8082  else {
8083  seq = 0;
8084  MScore::seq = 0;
8085  }
8086 //---
8087  //
8088  // avoid font problems by overriding the environment
8089  // fall back to "C" locale
8090  //
8091 
8092  //#ifndef Q_OS_WIN
8093  //setenv("LANG", "C", 1);
8094  //#endif
8095  //QLocale::setDefault(QLocale(QLocale::C));

8097  if (MScore::debugMode) {
8098  QStringList sl(QCoreApplication::libraryPaths());
8099  foreach(const QString& s, sl)
8100  qDebug("LibraryPath: <%s>", qPrintable(s));
8101  }
8102 
8103  // rastral size of font is 20pt = 20/72 inch = 20*DPI/72 dots
8104  // staff has 5 lines = 4 * _spatium
8105  // _spatium = SPATIUM20; // 20.0 / 72.0 * DPI / 4.0;
8106 
8107  if (!MScore::noGui) {
8108 #ifndef Q_OS_MAC
8109  qApp->setWindowIcon(*icons[int(Icons::window_ICON)]);
8110 #endif
8111  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing workspace…"));
8112  WorkspacesManager::initCurrentWorkspace();
8113  }
8114 
8115  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Creating main window…"));
8116  mscore = new MuseScore();
8117  // create a score for internal use
8118  gscore = new MasterScore();
8119  gscore->setPaletteMode(true);
8120  gscore->setMovements(new Movements());
8121  gscore->setStyle(MScore::baseStyle());
8122 
8123  gscore->style().set(Sid::MusicalTextFont, QString("Leland Text"));
8124  ScoreFont* scoreFont = ScoreFont::fontFactory("Leland");
8125  gscore->setScoreFont(scoreFont);
8126  gscore->setNoteHeadWidth(scoreFont->width(SymId::noteheadBlack, gscore->spatium()) / SPATIUM20);
8127 
8128 #ifndef TELEMETRY_DISABLED
8129  tryToRequestTelemetryPermission();
8130 #endif

8133  //read languages list
8134  mscore->readLanguages(mscoreGlobalShare + "locale/languages.xml");
8135 
8136  if (!MScore::noGui) {
8137  if (preferences.getBool(PREF_APP_STARTUP_FIRSTSTART)) {
8138  mscoreFirstStart = true;
8139  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing startup wizard…"));
8140  StartupWizard* sw = new StartupWizard;
8141  sw->exec();
8142  preferences.setPreference(PREF_APP_STARTUP_FIRSTSTART, false);
8143  preferences.setPreference(PREF_APP_KEYBOARDLAYOUT, sw->keyboardLayout());
8144  preferences.setPreference(PREF_UI_APP_LANGUAGE, sw->language());
8145  setMscoreLocale(sw->language());
8146  Workspace::writeGlobalToolBar();
8147  Workspace::writeGlobalGUIState();
8148  Workspace* targetWorkspace = WorkspacesManager::visibleWorkspaces()[0];
8149  if (targetWorkspace)
8150  mscore->changeWorkspace(targetWorkspace, true);
8151 
8152  preferences.setPreference(PREF_UI_APP_STARTUP_SHOWTOURS, sw->showTours());
8153  delete sw;
8154 
8155  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing preferences…"));
8156  // reinitialize preferences so some default values are calculated based on chosen language
8157  preferences.init();
8158  // store preferences with locale-dependent default values
8159  // so that the values from first start will be used later
8160  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYSCORES);
8161  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYSTYLES);
8162  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYIMAGES);
8163  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYTEMPLATES);
8164  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYPLUGINS);
8165  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYSOUNDFONTS);
8166  preferences.setToDefaultValue(PREF_APP_PATHS_MYEXTENSIONS);
8167  updateExternalValuesFromPreferences();
8168  }
8169  if (!Shortcut::customSource()) {
8170  QString keyboardLayout = preferences.getString(PREF_APP_KEYBOARDLAYOUT);
8171  StartupWizard::autoSelectShortcuts(keyboardLayout);
8172  }
8173  }
8174 
8175  if (!noSeq) {
8176  if (!seq->init())
8177  qDebug("sequencer init failed");
8178  }
8179 
8180  QApplication::instance()->installEventFilter(mscore);
8181 
8182 #ifndef TELEMETRY_DISABLED
8183  QApplication::instance()->installEventFilter(ActionEventObserver::instance());
8184  ActionEventObserver::instance()->setScoreState(mscore->state());
8185  QObject::connect(mscore, &MuseScore::scoreStateChanged, ActionEventObserver::instance(), &ActionEventObserver::setScoreState);
8186 #endif
8187 
8188  mscore->setRevision(Ms::revision);
8189  int files = 0;
8190  bool restoredSession = false;
8191 
8192  if (MScore::noGui)
8193  return;
8194  else {
8195  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing main window…"));
8196  mscore->readSettings();
8197  QObject::connect(qApp, SIGNAL(messageReceived(const QString&)),
8198  mscore, SLOT(handleMessage(const QString&)));
8199 
8200  static_cast<QtSingleApplication*>(qApp)->setActivationWindow(mscore, false);
8201  // count filenames specified on the command line
8202  // these are the non-empty strings remaining in argv
8203  foreach(const QString& name, argv) {
8204  if (!name.isEmpty())
8205  ++files;
8206  }
8207 #ifdef Q_OS_MAC
8208  // app->paths contains files requested to be loaded by OS X
8209  // append these to argv and update file count
8210  foreach(const QString& name, static_cast<MuseScoreApplication*>(qApp)->paths) {
8211  if (!name.isEmpty()) {
8212  argv << name;
8213  ++files;
8214  }
8215  }
8216 #endif
8217  //
8218  // TODO: delete old session backups
8219  //
8220  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Restoring session…"));
8221  restoredSession = mscore->restoreSession((preferences.sessionStart() == SessionStart::LAST && (files == 0)));
8222  }
8223 
8224  errorMessage = new QErrorMessage(mscore);
8225 #ifdef SCRIPT_INTERFACE
8226  mscore->getPluginManager()->readPluginList();
8227  mscore->loadPlugins();
8228 #endif
8229  mscore->writeSessionFile(false);
8230 
8231 #ifdef Q_OS_MAC
8232  // there's a bug in Qt showing the toolbar unified after switching
8233  // showFullScreen(), showMaximized(), showNormal()...
8234  mscore->setUnifiedTitleAndToolBarOnMac(false);
8235 
8236  // don't let macOS add "Show Tab Bar" to "View" Menu
8237  CocoaBridge::setAllowsAutomaticWindowTabbing(false);
8238 
8239  // Observe when macOS's Dark Mode is switched on or off and let MuseScore's
8240  // theme switch along with it if the user has chosen that setting
8241  CocoaBridge::observeDarkModeSwitches([]() {
8242  if (preferences.preferredGlobalStyle() == MuseScorePreferredStyleType::FOLLOW_SYSTEM)
8243  MuseScore::updateUiStyleAndTheme();
8244  });
8245 #endif
8246 
8247  mscore->changeState(mscore->noScore() ? STATE_DISABLED : STATE_NORMAL);
8248  mscore->show();
8249 
8250  if (!restoredSession || files) {
8251  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Loading scores…"));
8252  loadScores(argv);
8253  }
8254 
8255  if (mscore->hasToCheckForExtensionsUpdate())
8256  mscore->checkForExtensionsUpdate();
8257 
8258  if (QWidget* menubar = mscore->menuWidget())
8259  TourHandler::addWidgetToTour("welcome", menubar, "menubar");
8260 
8261  if (!scoresOnCommandline && preferences.getBool(PREF_UI_APP_STARTUP_SHOWSTARTCENTER) && (!restoredSession || mscore->scores().size() == 0)) {
8262  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing start center…"));
8263 #ifdef Q_OS_MAC
8264 // ugly, but on mac we get an event when a file is open.
8265 // We can't get the event when the startcenter is shown.
8266 // So we let the event loop run a bit before showing the start center.
8267  QTimer* timer = new QTimer();
8268  timer->setSingleShot(true);
8269  QObject::connect(timer, &QTimer::timeout, [=]() {
8270  if (!scoresOnCommandline) {
8271  getAction("startcenter")->setChecked(true);
8272  mscore->showStartcenter(true);
8273  }
8274  timer->deleteLater();
8275  } );
8276  timer->start(500);
8277 #else
8278 
8279  getAction("startcenter")->setChecked(true);
8280  mscore->showStartcenter(true);
8281 #endif
8282  }
8283  else {
8284  showSplashMessage(sc, tr("Initializing tours…"));
8285  mscore->tourHandler()->startTour("welcome");
8286  //otherwise, welcome tour will appear on closing StartCenter
8287  }
8288 
8289  if (sc) {
8290  sc->close();
8291  qApp->processEvents();
8292  }
8293 
8294  mscore->showPlayPanel(preferences.getBool(PREF_UI_APP_STARTUP_SHOWPLAYPANEL));
8295  QSettings settings;
8296  if (settings.value("synthControlVisible", false).toBool())
8297  mscore->showSynthControl(true);
8298  }
8299 
8300 
8301 bool MuseScore::saveScoreParts(const QString& inFilePath, const QString& outFilePath)
8302 {
8303  MasterScore* score = mscore->readScore(inFilePath);
8304  if (!score) {
8305  return false;
8306  }
8307 
8308  if (!styleFile.isEmpty()) {
8309  QFile f(styleFile);
8310  if (f.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly)) {
8311  score->style().load(&f);
8312  }
8313  }
8314  score->switchToPageMode();
8315 
8316  // if no parts, generate parts from existing instruments
8317  if (score->excerpts().isEmpty()) {
8318  auto excerpts = Excerpt::createAllExcerpt(score);
8319  for (Excerpt* e : excerpts) {
8320  Score* nscore = new Score(e->oscore());
8321  e->setPartScore(nscore);
8322  nscore->style().set(Sid::createMultiMeasureRests, true);
8323  auto excerptCmdFake = new AddExcerpt(e);
8324  excerptCmdFake->redo(nullptr);
8325  Excerpt::createExcerpt(e);
8326  }
8327  }
8328 
8329  QJsonArray partsObjList;
8330  QJsonArray partsMetaList;
8331  QJsonArray partsTitles;
8332 
8333  for (Excerpt* excerpt : score->excerpts()) {
8334  Score* part = excerpt->partScore();
8335  QMap<QString, QString> partMetaTags = part->metaTags();
8336 
8337  QJsonValue partTitle(part->title());
8338  partsTitles << partTitle;
8339 
8340  QVariantMap meta;
8341  for (const QString& key: partMetaTags.keys()) {
8342  meta[key] = partMetaTags[key];
8343  }
8344 
8345  QJsonValue partMetaObj = QJsonObject::fromVariantMap(meta);
8346  partsMetaList << partMetaObj;
8347 
8348  QJsonValue partObj(QString::fromLatin1(exportMsczAsJSON(part)));
8349  partsObjList << partObj;
8350  }
8351 
8352  QJsonObject json;
8353  json["parts"] = partsTitles;
8354  json["partsMeta"] = partsMetaList;
8355  json["partsBin"] = partsObjList;
8356 
8357  QJsonDocument jsonDoc(json);
8358  QFile out(outFilePath);
8359 
8360  bool res = out.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly);
8361  if (res) {
8362  out.write(jsonDoc.toJson(QJsonDocument::Compact));
8363  out.close();
8364  }
8365 
8366  delete score;
8367  return res;
8368 }
8369 
8370 QByteArray MuseScore::exportMsczAsJSON(Score* score)
8371 {
8372  QBuffer buffer;
8373  buffer.open(QIODevice::ReadWrite);
8374 
8375  QString fileName = saveFilename(score->title()) + ".mscz";
8376  score->saveCompressedFile(&buffer, fileName, false, true);
8377 
8378  buffer.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly);
8379  QByteArray scoreData = buffer.readAll();
8380  buffer.close();
8381 
8382  return scoreData.toBase64();
8383 }
8384 
8385 //---------------------------------------------------------
8386 // exportPartsPdfsToJSON
8387 //---------------------------------------------------------
8388 
8389 bool MuseScore::exportPartsPdfsToJSON(const QString& inFilePath, const QString& outFilePath)
8390 {
8391  MasterScore* score = mscore->readScore(inFilePath);
8392  if (!score)
8393  return false;
8394 
8395  QString outPath = QFileInfo(inFilePath).path() + "/";
8396 
8397  QJsonObject jsonForPdfs;
8398  QString outName = outPath + QFileInfo(inFilePath).completeBaseName() + ".pdf";
8399  jsonForPdfs["score"] = outName;
8400 
8401  //save score pdf
8402  if (!styleFile.isEmpty()) {
8403  QFile f(styleFile);
8404  if (f.open(QIODevice::ReadOnly))
8405  score->style().load(&f);
8406  }
8407  score->switchToPageMode();
8408 
8409  jsonForPdfs["scoreBin"] = QString::fromLatin1(mscore->exportPdfAsJSON(score));
8410 
8411  //save extended score+parts and separate parts pdfs
8412  //if no parts, generate parts from existing instruments
8413  if (score->excerpts().size() == 0) {
8414  auto excerpts = Excerpt::createAllExcerpt(score);
8415  for (Excerpt* e : excerpts) {
8416  Score* nscore = new Score(e->oscore());
8417  e->setPartScore(nscore);
8418  nscore->style().set(Sid::createMultiMeasureRests, true);
8419  auto excerptCmdFake = new AddExcerpt(e);
8420  excerptCmdFake->redo(nullptr);
8421  Excerpt::createExcerpt(e);
8422  }
8423  }
8424 
8425  QList<Score*> scores;
8426  scores.append(score);
8427  QJsonArray partsArray;
8428  QJsonArray partsNamesArray;
8429  for (Excerpt* e : score->excerpts()) {
8430  scores.append(e->partScore());
8431  QJsonValue partNameVal(e->title());
8432  partsNamesArray.append(partNameVal);
8433  QJsonValue partVal(QString::fromLatin1(exportPdfAsJSON(e->partScore())));
8434  partsArray.append(partVal);
8435  }
8436  jsonForPdfs["parts"] = partsNamesArray;
8437  jsonForPdfs["partsBin"] = partsArray;
8438 
8439  jsonForPdfs["scoreFullPostfix"] = QString("-Score_and_parts") + ".pdf";
8440 
8441  QTemporaryFile tempPdf;
8442  tempPdf.open();
8443 
8444  bool res = mscore->savePdf(scores, tempPdf.fileName());
8445  QByteArray fullScoreData = tempPdf.readAll();
8446 
8447  jsonForPdfs["scoreFullBin"] = QString::fromLatin1(fullScoreData.toBase64());
8448 
8449  QJsonDocument jsonDoc(jsonForPdfs);
8450  const QString& jsonPath{outFilePath};
8451  QFile file(jsonPath);
8452  res &= file.open(QIODevice::WriteOnly);
8453  if (res) {
8454  file.write(jsonDoc.toJson(QJsonDocument::Compact));
8455  file.close();
8456  }
8457 
8458  delete score;
8459  return res;
8460  }
